name: gfalse
description: This command is an alias of GNU `false`.

name: gfgrep
description: This command is an alias of GNU `fgrep`.

name: gfind
description: This command is an alias of GNU `find`.

name: gfmt
description: This command is an alias of GNU `fmt`.

name: gfold
description: This command is an alias of GNU `fold`.

name: gfortran
description: Preprocess and compile Fortran source files, then assemble and link them together. More information: <https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gfortran/Invoking-GNU-Fortran.html>.

name: gftp
description: This command is an alias of GNU `ftp`.

name: ggrep
description: This command is an alias of GNU `grep`.

name: ggroups
description: This command is an alias of GNU `groups`.

name: gh
description: Work seamlessly with GitHub. Some subcommands such as `config` have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh>.

name: gh-a11y
description: This command is an alias of `gh accessibility`.

name: gh-accessibility
description: Learn about GitHub CLI's accessibility experiences. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/>.

name: gh-agent
description: This command is an alias of `gh agent-task`.

name: gh-agent-task
description: Manage GitHub agent tasks. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_agent-task>.

name: gh-alias
description: Manage GitHub CLI command aliases. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_alias>.

name: gh-api
description: Make authenticated HTTP requests to the GitHub API and print the response. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_api>.

name: gh-at
description: This command is an alias of `gh attestation`.

name: gh-attestation
description: Download and verify artifact attestations to ensure their integrity and provenance. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_attestation>.

name: gh-auth
description: Authenticate with a GitHub host. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_auth>.

name: gh-browse
description: Open a GitHub repository in the browser or print the URL. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_browse>.

name: gh-cache
description: Manage GitHub Actions caches. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_cache>.

name: gh-codespace
description: Connect and manage your codespaces in GitHub. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_codespace>.

name: gh-completion
description: Generate shell completion scripts for GitHub CLI commands. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_completion>.

name: gh-config
description: Change configuration for GitHub CLI. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_config>.

name: gh-copilot
description: Interact with GitHub Copilot. Note: Deprecated in favor of `copilot`. More information: <https://github.com/github/gh-copilot#usage>.

name: gh-cs
description: This command is an alias of `gh codespace`.

name: gh-environment
description: Display help about environment variables for the GitHub CLI command. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_help_environment>.

name: gh-extension
description: Manage extensions for the GitHub CLI. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_extension>.

name: gh-formatting
description: Formatting options for JSON data exported from gh GitHub CLI command. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_help_formatting>.

name: gh-gist
description: Work with GitHub Gists. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_gist>.

name: gh-gpg-key
description: Manage GPG keys registered with the authorized GitHub account. See also: `gpg`. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_gpg-key>.

name: gh-help
description: Display help about the GitHub CLI command. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_help>.

name: gh-issue
description: Manage GitHub issues. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_issue>.

name: gh-issue-create
description: Create GitHub issues on a repository. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_issue_create>.

name: gh-label
description: Work with GitHub labels. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_label>.

name: gh-mintty
description: Display help about MinTTY integration for the GitHub CLI command. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_help_mintty>.

name: gh-org
description: Work with GitHub organizations. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_org>.

name: gh-pr
description: Manage GitHub pull requests. Some subcommands such as `create` have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_pr>.

name: gh-pr-checks
description: View CI checks for a GitHub pull request. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_pr_checks>.

name: gh-pr-comment
description: Add a comment to a GitHub pull request. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_pr_comment>.

name: gh-pr-create
description: Manage GitHub pull requests. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_pr_create>.

name: gh-pr-merge
description: Merge a GitHub pull request. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_pr_merge>.

name: gh-pr-view
description: View details of a GitHub pull request. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_pr_view>.

name: gh-preview
description: Preview GitHub CLI programs for testing and development purposes. These commands are unstable and may change at any time. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_preview>.

name: gh-project
description: Work with GitHub Projects. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_project>.

name: gh-reference
description: Display a reference about the GitHub CLI command. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_help_reference>.

name: gh-release
description: Manage GitHub releases. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_release>.

name: gh-repo
description: Work with GitHub repositories. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_repo>.

name: gh-repo-create
description: Create a new GitHub repository. Note: `--public`, `--private`, or `--internal` is required when not running interactively. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_repo_create>.

name: gh-rs
description: This command is an alias of `gh ruleset`.

name: gh-ruleset
description: Manage GitHub repository rulesets. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_ruleset>.

name: gh-run
description: View, run, and watch recent GitHub Actions workflow runs. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_run>.

name: gh-screensaver
description: Extension for GitHub CLI that runs animated terminal screensavers. See also: `gh extension`. More information: <https://github.com/vilmibm/gh-screensaver>.

name: gh-search
description: Search across all of GitHub. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_search>.

name: gh-secret
description: Manage GitHub secrets. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_secret>.

name: gh-secret-set
description: Create or update GitHub secrets. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_secret_set>.

name: gh-skyline
description: Generate a 3D model of your GitHub contribution history. By default, it will create a `{username}-{year}-github-skyline.stl` file in the current directory. More information: <https://github.com/github/gh-skyline>.

name: gh-ssh-key
description: Manage GitHub SSH keys. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_ssh-key>.

name: gh-status
description: Check the status of subscribed repositories on GitHub. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_status>.

name: gh-variable
description: Manage GitHub Actions and Dependabot variables. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_variable>.

name: gh-workflow
description: List, view, and run GitHub Actions workflows. More information: <https://cli.github.com/manual/gh_workflow>.

name: ghc
description: The Glasgow Haskell Compiler. Compiles and links Haskell source files. More information: <https://downloads.haskell.org/ghc/latest/docs/users_guide/usage.html>.

name: ghci
description: The Glasgow Haskell Compiler's interactive environment. More information: <https://downloads.haskell.org/ghc/latest/docs/users_guide/ghci.html>.

name: ghcid
description: Simple and efficient CLI IDE for Haskell that reloads code on file changes. Continuously displays compile errors, warnings, and test results. More information: <https://github.com/ndmitchell/ghcid>.

name: ghcup
description: Haskell toolchain installer. Install, manage, and update Haskell toolchains. More information: <https://gitlab.haskell.org/haskell/ghcup-hs>.

name: ghdl
description: Open-source simulator for the VHDL language. More information: <https://ghdl.github.io/ghdl/>.

name: ghead
description: This command is an alias of GNU `head`.

name: ghost
description: A blogging platform and headless CMS. More information: <https://docs.ghost.org/ghost-cli>.

name: ghostid
description: This command is an alias of GNU `hostid`.

name: ghostname
description: This command is an alias of GNU `hostname`.

name: ghostty
description: A fast, feature-rich, and cross-platform terminal emulator that uses platform-native UI and GPU acceleration. Note: All options from the configuration file can also be used on the command-line (using `--option=argument`). More information: <https://ghostty.org/docs/config/reference>.

name: ghq
description: Manage remote repository clones organized by hostname and path. More information: <https://github.com/x-motemen/ghq>.

name: ghy
description: This command is an alias of `Get-History`.

name: gibo
description: Fetch gitignore boilerplates. More information: <https://github.com/simonwhitaker/gibo>.

name: gid
description: This command is an alias of GNU `id`.

name: gif2webp
description: Convert a GIF image to WebP. More information: <https://developers.google.com/speed/webp/docs/gif2webp>.

name: gifconfig
description: This command is an alias of GNU `ifconfig`.

name: gifdiff
description: Compare two GIFs for identical visual appearance. See also: `gifsicle`. More information: <https://www.lcdf.org/gifsicle/>.

name: gifsicle
description: Create, edit, manipulate, and get information about GIF files. More information: <https://www.lcdf.org/gifsicle/>.

name: giftopnm
description: Convert a GIF file into a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/giftopnm.html>.

name: gimp
description: GNU image manipulation program. See also: `krita`. More information: <https://docs.gimp.org/en/gimp-fire-up.html#gimp-concepts-running-command-line>.

name: gindent
description: This command is an alias of GNU `indent`.

name: ginstall
description: This command is an alias of GNU `install`.

name: gio
description: Handle local and virtual files (GVfs). Part of GLib used in GNOME-based systems. More information: <https://manned.org/gio>.

name: gio-trash
description: Move files to the trash bin. Used by GNOME to handle trash. More information: <https://manned.org/gio>.

name: gist
description: Upload code to <https://gist.github.com>. More information: <https://github.com/defunkt/gist>.

name: git
description: Distributed version control system. Some subcommands such as `commit`, `add`, `branch`, `switch`, `push`, etc. have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git>.

name: git-abort
description: Abort an ongoing rebase, merge, or cherry-pick. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-abort>.

name: git-add
description: Adds changed files to the index. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-add>.

name: git-alias
description: Create shortcuts for Git commands. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-alias>.

name: git-am
description: Apply patch files and create a commit. Useful when receiving commits via email. See also: `git format-patch` which can generate patch files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-am>.

name: git-annex
description: Manage files with Git, without checking their contents in. When a file is annexed, its content is moved into a key-value store, and a symlink is made that points to the content. More information: <https://git-annex.branchable.com/git-annex/>.

name: git-annotate
description: Show commit hash and last author on each line of a file. See `git blame`, which is preferred over `git annotate`. `git annotate` is provided for those familiar with other version control systems. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-annotate>.

name: git-apply
description: Apply a patch to files and/or to the index without creating a commit. See also: `git am` which applies a patch and also creates a commit. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-apply>.

name: git-archive
description: Create an archive of files from a tree. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-archive>.

name: git-archive-file
description: Export all the files of the current Git branch into a Zip archive. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-archive-file>.

name: git-authors
description: Generate a list of committers of a Git repository. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-authors>.

name: git-bisect
description: Use binary search to find the commit that introduced a bug. Git automatically jumps back and forth in the commit graph to progressively narrow down the faulty commit. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-bisect>.

name: git-blame
description: Show commit hash and last author on each line of a file. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-blame>.

name: git-blame-someone-else
description: Blame someone else for your bad code. More information: <https://github.com/jayphelps/git-blame-someone-else>.

name: git-branch
description: Main Git command for working with branches. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-branch>.

name: git-browse
description: View an upstream repository in the default browser. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-browse>.

name: git-browse-ci
description: Open the current Git repository's CI website in the default web browser. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-browse-ci>.

name: git-brv
description: Print a list of branches, sorted by last commit date. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-brv>.

name: git-bug
description: A distributed bug tracker that uses Git's internal storage, so no files are added in your project. You may submit your problems to the same Git remote you use to interact with others, much like commits and branches. More information: <https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/blob/master/doc/md/git-bug.md>.

name: git-bugreport
description: Captures debug information from the system and user, generating a text file to aid in the reporting of a bug in Git. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-bugreport>.

name: git-bulk
description: Execute operations on multiple Git repositories. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-bulk>.

name: git-bundle
description: Package objects and references into an archive. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-bundle>.

name: git-cat-file
description: Provide content or type and size information for Git repository objects. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-cat-file>.

name: git-changelog
description: Generate a changelog report from repository commits and tags. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-changelog>.

name: git-check-attr
description: For every pathname, list if each attribute is unspecified, set, or unset as a gitattribute on that pathname. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-check-attr>.

name: git-check-ignore
description: Analyze and debug Git ignore/exclude (`.gitignore`) files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-check-ignore>.

name: git-check-mailmap
description: Show canonical names and email addresses of contacts. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-check-mailmap>.

name: git-check-ref-format
description: Check if a reference name is acceptable, and exit with a non-zero status if it is not. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-check-ref-format>.

name: git-checkout
description: Checkout a branch or paths to the working tree. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-checkout>.

name: git-checkout-index
description: Copy files from the index to the working tree. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-checkout-index>.

name: git-cherry
description: Find commits that have yet to be applied upstream. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-cherry>.

name: git-cherry-pick
description: Apply the changes introduced by existing commits to the current branch. To apply changes to another branch, first use `git checkout` to switch to the desired branch. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-cherry-pick>.

name: git-clean
description: Remove files not tracked by Git from the working tree. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-clean>.

name: git-clear
description: Clear a Git working directory as if it was freshly cloned with the current branch including files in `.gitignore`. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-clear>.

name: git-clear-soft
description: Clear a Git working directory as if it was freshly cloned with the current branch excluding files in `.gitignore`. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-clear-soft>.

name: git-cliff
description: A highly customizable changelog generator. More information: <https://git-cliff.org/docs/usage/args/>.

name: git-clone
description: Clone an existing repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-clone>.

name: git-coauthor
description: Add another author to the latest commit. Since this command rewrites the Git history, `--force` will be needed when pushing next time. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-coauthor>.

name: git-cola
description: A powerful Git GUI with a slick and intuitive user interface. More information: <https://git-cola.readthedocs.io/en/latest/git-cola.html>.

name: git-column
description: Display data in columns. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-column>.

name: git-commit
description: Commit files to the repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-commit>.

name: git-commit-graph
description: Write and verify Git commit-graph files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-commit-graph>.

name: git-commit-tree
description: Low level utility to create commit objects. See also: `git commit`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-commit-tree>.

name: git-commits-since
description: Display commits since a time or date. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-commits-since>.

name: git-config
description: Manage custom configuration options for Git repositories. These configurations can be local (for the current repository) or global (for the current user). More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-config>.

name: git-contrib
description: Display commits from an author. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-contrib>.

name: git-count
description: Print the total number of commits. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-count>.

name: git-count-objects
description: Count the number of unpacked objects and their disk consumption. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-count-objects>.

name: git-cp
description: Copy an existing file to a new location, preserving history. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-cp>.

name: git-create-branch
description: Create a Git branch in a repository. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-create-branch>.

name: git-credential
description: Retrieve and store user credentials. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-credential>.

name: git-credential-cache
description: Git helper to temporarily store passwords in memory. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-credential-cache>.

name: git-credential-store
description: Git helper to store passwords on disk. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-credential-store>.

name: git-cvsexportcommit
description: Export a single `Git` commit to a CVS checkout. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-cvsexportcommit>.

name: git-daemon
description: A really simple server for Git repositories. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-daemon>.

name: git-delete-branch
description: Delete local and remote Git branches. Part of `git-extras`. If deleting the checked out branch, only the remote branch will be deleted. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-delete-branch>.

name: git-delete-merged-branches
description: Delete branches that are listed in `git branch --merged` excluding master. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-delete-merged-branches>.

name: git-delete-squashed-branches
description: Delete branches that have been "squashed-merged" into a specified branch and checkout. If no branch is specified, default to the currently checked out branch. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-delete-squashed-branches>.

name: git-delete-submodule
description: Delete a submodule from a Git repository. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-delete-submodule>.

name: git-delete-tag
description: Delete existing local and remote tags. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-delete-tag>.

name: git-delta
description: List files that differ from another branch. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-delta>.

name: git-describe
description: Give an object a human-readable name based on an available ref. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-describe>.

name: git-diff
description: Show changes to tracked files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-diff>.

name: git-diff-files
description: Compare files using their sha1 hashes and modes. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-diff-files>.

name: git-diff-index
description: Compare the working directory with a commit or tree object. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-diff-index>.

name: git-diff-tree
description: Compares the content and mode of blobs found via two tree objects. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-diff-tree>.

name: git-difftool
description: Show file changes using external diff tools. Accepts the same options and arguments as `git diff`. See also: `git diff`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-difftool>.

name: git-effort
description: Display how much activity a file has had, showing commits per file and "active days" i.e. total number of days that contributed to the file. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-effort>.

name: git-extras
description: Git extension pack. More information: <https://manned.org/git-extras>.

name: git-fame
description: Pretty-print Git repository contributions. More information: <https://manned.org/git-fame>.

name: git-fast-export
description: Export the contents and history of a Git repository in a streamable, plain-text format. More information: <https://manned.org/git-fast-export>.

name: git-feature
description: Create or merge feature branches. Feature branches obey the format feature/name. More information: <https://manned.org/git-feature>.

name: git-fetch
description: Download objects and refs from a remote repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-fetch>.

name: git-filter-branch
description: Change branch history, like removing files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-filter-branch>.

name: git-filter-repo
description: A versatile tool for rewriting Git history. See also: `bfg`. More information: <https://github.com/newren/git-filter-repo>.

name: git-flow
description: A collection of Git extensions to provide high-level repository operations. More information: <https://github.com/nvie/gitflow>.

name: git-for-each-ref
description: List and optionally format references (branches, tags) in a Git repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-for-each-ref>.

name: git-for-each-repo
description: Run a Git command on a list of repositories. Note: This command is experimental and may change. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-for-each-repo>.

name: git-force-clone
description: Get the basic functionality of `git clone`, but if the destination Git repository already exists it will force-reset it to resemble a clone of the remote. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-force-clone>.

name: git-fork
description: Fork a GitHub repo. Like `git clone` but forks first. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-fork>.

name: git-format-patch
description: Prepare `.patch` files. Useful when emailing commits elsewhere. See also: `git am` which can apply generated `.patch` files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-format-patch>.

name: git-fresh-branch
description: Create an empty local branch. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md##git-fresh-branch>.

name: git-fsck
description: Verify the validity and connectivity of nodes in a Git repository index. Does not make any modifications. See also: `git gc` for cleaning up dangling blobs. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-fsck>.

name: git-gc
description: Optimise the local repository by cleaning unnecessary files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-gc>.

name: git-get-tar-commit-id
description: Extract commit ID from an archive created using `git archive`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-get-tar-commit-id>.

name: git-gh-pages
description: Create a new branch inside the current repository called `gh-pages`. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-gh-pages>.

name: git-graft
description: Merge commits from a branch into another branch and delete the source branch. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-graft>.

name: git-grep
description: Find strings inside tracked files in a repository. Accepts a lot of the same flags as regular `grep`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-grep>.

name: git-gui
description: A GUI for Git to manage branches, commits, and remotes, and perform local merges. See also: `git-cola`, `gitk`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-gui>.

name: git-guilt
description: Show total blame count for files with unstaged changes or calculate the change in blame between two revisions. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-guilt>.

name: git-hash-object
description: Computes the unique hash key of content and optionally creates an object with specified type. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-hash-object>.

name: git-help
description: Display help information about Git. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-help>.

name: git-ignore
description: Show/update `.gitignore` files. Part of `git-extras`. See also: `git ignore-io`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-ignore>.

name: git-ignore-io
description: Generate `.gitignore` files from predefined templates. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-ignore-io>.

name: git-imerge
description: Perform a merge or rebase between two Git branches incrementally. Conflicts between branches are tracked down to pairs of individual commits, to simplify conflict resolution. More information: <https://github.com/mhagger/git-imerge>.

name: git-info
description: Display Git repository information. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-info>.

name: git-init
description: Initialize a new local Git repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-init>.

name: git-instaweb
description: Helper to launch a GitWeb server. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-instaweb>.

name: git-lfs
description: Work with large files in Git repositories. More information: <https://github.com/git-lfs/git-lfs/tree/main/docs>.

name: git-lfs-transfer
description: Server-side implementation of the Git LFS pure SSH transfer protocol. Allows Git LFS to upload and download large files over SSH instead of HTTPS. More information: <https://github.com/charmbracelet/git-lfs-transfer#usage>.

name: git-local-commits
description: Show local commits that haven't been pushed to origin. Any additional arguments will be passed directly to `git log`. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-local-commits>.

name: git-lock
description: Lock a file in a Git repository from being modified by a commit. Part of `git-extras`. See also: `git-unlock`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-lock>.

name: git-locked
description: List locked files in a Git repository. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-locked>.

name: git-log
description: Show a history of commits. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-log>.

name: git-ls-files
description: Show information about files in the index and the working tree. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-ls-files>.

name: git-ls-remote
description: Git command for listing references in a remote repository based on name or URL. If no name or URL are given, then the configured upstream branch will be used, or remote origin if the former is not configured. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-ls-remote>.

name: git-ls-tree
description: List the contents of a tree object. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-ls-tree>.

name: git-magic
description: Automate add, commit, and push routines. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-magic>.

name: git-mailinfo
description: Extract patch and authorship information from a single email message. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-mailinfo>.

name: git-maintenance
description: Run tasks to optimize Git repository data. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-maintenance>.

name: git-merge
description: Merge branches. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-merge>.

name: git-merge-base
description: Find a common ancestor of two commits. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-merge-base>.

name: git-merge-index
description: Run a merge program on files that need merging. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-merge-index>.

name: git-merge-into
description: Merge one branch into another branch. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-merge-into>.

name: git-merge-one-file
description: Resolve a single file merge after a trivial merge. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-merge-one-file>.

name: git-merge-repo
description: Merge two repository histories. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-merge-repo>.

name: git-merge-tree
description: Merge branches without changing files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-merge-tree>.

name: git-mergetool
description: Run merge conflict resolution tools to resolve merge conflicts. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-mergetool>.

name: git-missing
description: Show commits which aren't shared between two branches. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-missing>.

name: git-mktree
description: Build a tree object using `ls-tree` formatted text. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-mktree>.

name: git-mr
description: Check out GitLab merge requests locally. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-mr>.

name: git-mv
description: Move or rename files and update the Git index. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-mv>.

name: git-name-rev
description: Describe a commit using existing ref names. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-name-rev>.

name: git-notes
description: Add or inspect object notes. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-notes>.

name: git-obliterate
description: Delete files and erase their history from a Git repository. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-obliterate>.

name: git-p4
description: Import from and submit to Perforce repositories. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-p4>.

name: git-paste
description: Send commits to a pastebin site using `pastebinit`. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-paste>.

name: git-pr
description: Check out GitHub pull requests locally. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-pr>.

name: git-prune
description: Git command for pruning all unreachable objects from the object database. This command is often not used directly but as an internal command that is used by Git gc. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-prune>.

name: git-psykorebase
description: Rebase a branch on top of another using a merge commit and only one conflict handling. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-psykorebase>.

name: git-pull
description: Fetch branch from a remote repository and merge it to local repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-pull>.

name: git-pull-request
description: Create a pull request for a project on GitHub. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-pull-request>.

name: git-push
description: Push commits to a remote repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-push>.

name: git-range-diff
description: Compare two commit ranges (e.g. two versions of a branch). More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-range-diff>.

name: git-reauthor
description: Change details about an author identity. Since this command rewrites the Git history, `--force` will be needed when pushing next time. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-reauthor>.

name: git-rebase
description: Reapply commits from one branch on top of another branch. Commonly used to "move" an entire branch to another base, creating copies of the commits in the new location. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-rebase>.

name: git-rebase-patch
description: Find the commit the patch applies to and do a rebase. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-rebase-patch>.

name: git-reflog
description: Show a log of changes to local references like HEAD, branches, or tags. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-reflog>.

name: git-release
description: Create a Git tag for a release. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-release>.

name: git-remote
description: Manage set of tracked repositories ("remotes"). More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-remote>.

name: git-rename-branch
description: Rename a Git branch. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-rename-branch>.

name: git-rename-remote
description: Change remote for pulling and pushing. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-rename-remote>.

name: git-rename-tag
description: Rename a Git tag. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-rename-tag>.

name: git-repack
description: Pack unpacked objects in a Git repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-repack>.

name: git-repl
description: Git REPL (read-evaluate-print-loop) - an interactive Git shell. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-repl>.

name: git-replace
description: Create, list, and delete refs to replace objects. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-replace>.

name: git-request-pull
description: Generate a request asking the upstream project to pull changes into its tree. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-request-pull>.

name: git-rerere
description: Reuse fixes for merge conflicts. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-rerere>.

name: git-reset
description: Undo commits or unstage changes by resetting the current Git HEAD to the specified state. If a path is passed, it works as "unstage"; if a commit hash or branch is passed, it works as "uncommit". More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-reset>.

name: git-reset-file
description: Revert a file to `HEAD` or a commit. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-reset-file>.

name: git-restore
description: Restore working tree files. Requires Git version 2.23+. See also: `git checkout`, `git reset`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-restore>.

name: git-rev-list
description: List revisions (commits) in reverse chronological order. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-rev-list>.

name: git-rev-parse
description: Display metadata related to revisions. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-rev-parse>.

name: git-revert
description: Create new commits which reverse the effect of earlier ones. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-revert>.

name: git-rm
description: Remove files from repository index and local filesystem. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-rm>.

name: git-root
description: Print the root directory of the current Git repository. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-root>.

name: git-rscp
description: Reverse `git scp` - copy files from the working directory of a remote repository to the current working tree. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-scp>.

name: git-scp
description: Copy files from the current working tree to the working directory of a remote repository. Part of `git-extras`. Uses `rsync` to transfer files. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-scp>.

name: git-secret
description: Stores private data inside a Git repository. Written in Bash. More information: <https://github.com/sobolevn/git-secret>.

name: git-sed
description: Replace patterns in git-controlled files using sed. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-sed>.

name: git-send-email
description: Send a collection of patches as emails. Patches can be specified as files, directions, or a revision list. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-send-email>.

name: git-setup
description: Create a Git repository in a directory and commit all files. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-setup>.

name: git-shortlog
description: Summarizes the `git log` output. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-shortlog>.

name: git-show
description: Show various types of Git objects (commits, tags, etc.). More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-show>.

name: git-show-branch
description: Show branches and their commits. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-show-branch>.

name: git-show-index
description: Show the packed archive index of a Git repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-show-index>.

name: git-show-merged-branches
description: Print all branches which are merged into the current head. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-show-merged-branches>.

name: git-show-ref
description: Git command for listing references. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-show-ref>.

name: git-show-tree
description: Show a decorated tree graph with all branches of a Git repository, showing annotations. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-show-tree>.

name: git-show-unmerged-branches
description: Print all branches which are not merged into the current `HEAD`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-show-unmerged-branches>.

name: git-sizer
description: Computes various Git repository size metrics and alerts you to any that might cause problems or inconvenience. More information: <https://github.com/github/git-sizer>.

name: git-sparse-checkout
description: Check out only part of a repository's files instead of cloning or checking out everything. More information: <https://manned.org/git-sparse-checkout>.

name: git-squash
description: Squash multiple commits into a single commit. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-squash>.

name: git-stage
description: This command is an alias of `git add`.

name: git-stamp
description: Stamp the last commit message, with the possibility to reference the issues numbers from your bug tracker or link to its review page. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-stamp>.

name: git-standup
description: See commits from a specified user. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-standup>.

name: git-stash
description: Stash local Git changes in a temporary area. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-stash>.

name: git-status
description: Show the changes to files in a Git repository. List changed, added, and deleted files compared to the currently checked-out commit. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-status>.

name: git-stripspace
description: Read text (e.g. commit messages, notes, tags, and branch descriptions) from `stdin` and clean it into the manner used by Git. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-stripspace>.

name: git-submodule
description: Inspect, update, and manage submodules. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-submodule>.

name: git-subtree
description: Merge subtrees together or split repository into subtrees. More information: <https://manned.org/git-subtree>.

name: git-summary
description: Display information about a Git repository. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-summary>.

name: git-svn
description: Bidirectional operation between a Subversion repository and Git. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-svn>.

name: git-switch
description: Switch between Git branches. Requires Git version 2.23+. See also: `git checkout`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-switch>.

name: git-symbolic-ref
description: Read, change, or delete files that store references. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-symbolic-ref>.

name: git-sync
description: Sync local branches with remote branches. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://manned.org/git-sync>.

name: git-tag
description: Create, list, delete, or verify tags. A tag is a static reference to a commit. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-tag>.

name: git-touch
description: Create new files and add them to the index. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-touch>.

name: git-undo
description: Undo recent commits. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-undo>.

name: git-unlock
description: Unlock a file in a Git repository so it can be modified by a commit. Part of `git-extras`. See also: `git lock`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-unlock>.

name: git-unpack-file
description: Create a temporary file with a blob's contents. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-unpack-file>.

name: git-update-index
description: Git command for manipulating the index. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-update-index>.

name: git-update-ref
description: Git command for creating, updating, and deleting Git refs. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-update-ref>.

name: git-utimes
description: Change files modification time to their last commit date. Does not touch files that are in the working tree or index. Part of `git-extras`. More information: <https://github.com/tj/git-extras/blob/master/Commands.md#git-utimes>.

name: git-var
description: Print a Git logical variable's value. See `git config`, which is preferred over `git var`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-var>.

name: git-verify-commit
description: Check for GPG verification of commits. If no commits are verified, nothing will be printed, regardless of options specified. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-verify-commit>.

name: git-verify-pack
description: Verify packed Git archive files. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-verify-pack>.

name: git-verify-tag
description: Check for GPG verification of tags. If a tag wasn't signed, an error will occur. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-verify-tag>.

name: git-whatchanged
description: Show what has changed with recent commits or files. See also: `git log`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-whatchanged>.

name: git-worktree
description: Manage multiple working trees attached to the same repository. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-worktree>.

name: git-write-tree
description: Low level utility to create a tree object from the current index. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/git-write-tree>.

name: gitea
description: Administer Gitea, a lightweight Git hosting server. Requires a configured `app.ini` file or environment variables. More information: <https://docs.gitea.com/administration/command-line>.

name: github-label-sync
description: Synchronize GitHub labels. More information: <https://github.com/Financial-Times/github-label-sync>.

name: gitk
description: Browse Git repositories graphically. See also: `git-gui`, `git-cola`, `tig`. More information: <https://git-scm.com/docs/gitk>.

name: gitlab
description: Ruby wrapper for the GitLab API. Some subcommands such as `ctl` have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://narkoz.github.io/gitlab/>.

name: gitlab-backup
description: Manage backups for a GitLab Omnibus installation. See also: `gitlab-ctl`, `gitlab-runner`. More information: <https://docs.gitlab.com/administration/backup_restore/backup_gitlab/>.

name: gitlab-ctl
description: Manage the GitLab omnibus. More information: <https://docs.gitlab.com/omnibus/maintenance/>.

name: gitlab-runner
description: Manage GitLab runners. More information: <https://docs.gitlab.com/runner/>.

name: gitleaks
description: Detect secrets and API keys leaked in Git repositories. More information: <https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks#usage>.

name: gitlint
description: Git commit message linter checks your commit messages for style. More information: <https://jorisroovers.com/gitlint/>.

name: gitmoji
description: Interactively insert emojis on commits. More information: <https://github.com/carloscuesta/gitmoji-cli>.

name: gitsome
description: A terminal-based interface for GitHub, accessed via the `gh` command. It also provides menu-style autocomplete suggestions for `git` commands. More information: <https://github.com/donnemartin/gitsome#index>.

name: gitstats
description: Git repository statistics generator. More information: <https://gitstats.readthedocs.io/en/stable/getting-started.html#command-line-usage>.

name: gitui
description: A lightweight keyboard-only TUI for Git. See also: `tig`, `git-gui`. More information: <https://github.com/gitui-org/gitui>.

name: gitwatch
description: Automatically commit file or directory changes to a Git repository. More information: <https://github.com/gitwatch/gitwatch>.

name: gixy
description: Analyze nginx configuration files. More information: <https://github.com/yandex/gixy>.

name: gjoin
description: This command is an alias of GNU `join`.

name: gkill
description: This command is an alias of GNU `kill`.

name: gksu
description: Frontend for `su`. Allows you to run graphical commands which need root access without having to run an X terminal emulator. Note: This command is deprecated in favor of commands like `pkexec`, and is no longer maintained. See also: `gksudo`. More information: <https://manned.org/gksu>.

name: gksudo
description: Frontend for `sudo`. Allows you to run graphical commands which need root access without having to run an X terminal emulator. Note: This command is deprecated in favor of commands like `pkexec`, and is no longer maintained. See also: `gksu`. More information: <https://manned.org/gksudo>.

name: gl
description: In PowerShell, this command is an alias of `Get-Location`.

name: glab
description: Work seamlessly with GitLab. Some subcommands such as `config` have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/tree/main/docs/source>.

name: glab-alias
description: Manage GitLab CLI command aliases. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/alias/_index.md>.

name: glab-auth
description: Authenticate with a GitLab host. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/auth/_index.md>.

name: glab-issue
description: Manage GitLab issues. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/issue/_index.md>.

name: glab-mr
description: Manage GitLab merge requests. Some subcommands such as `create` have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/mr/_index.md>.

name: glab-mr-create
description: Manage GitLab merge requests. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/mr/create.md>.

name: glab-mr-merge
description: Merge GitLab merge requests. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/mr/merge.md>.

name: glab-pipeline
description: List, view, and run GitLab CI/CD pipelines. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/_index.md>.

name: glab-release
description: Manage GitLab releases. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/release/_index.md>.

name: glab-repo
description: Work with GitLab repositories. More information: <https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/cli/-/blob/main/docs/source/repo/_index.md>.

name: gladtex
description: A LaTeX formula preprocessor for HTML files. It converts LaTeX formulas to images. More information: <https://manned.org/gladtex>.

name: glances
description: A cross-platform system monitoring tool. See also: `htop`, `atop`, `top`, `btm`, `btop`. More information: <https://nicolargo.github.io/glances/>.

name: gleam
description: The compiler, build tool, package manager, and code formatter for Gleam, "a friendly language for building type-safe systems that scale!". More information: <https://gleam.run/writing-gleam/command-line-reference/>.

name: glib-compile-resources
description: Compiles resource files (e.g. images) into a binary resource bundle. These may be linked into GTK applications using the GResource API. More information: <https://manned.org/glib-compile-resources>.

name: glibtool
description: This command is an alias of GNU `libtool`.

name: glibtoolize
description: This command is an alias of GNU `libtoolize`.

name: glink
description: This command is an alias of GNU `link`.

name: gln
description: This command is an alias of GNU `ln`.

name: glocate
description: This command is an alias of GNU `locate`.

name: glogger
description: This command is an alias of GNU `logger`.

name: glogname
description: This command is an alias of GNU `logname`.

name: glow
description: Render Markdown in the terminal. More information: <https://manned.org/glow>.

name: gls
description: This command is an alias of GNU `ls`.

name: glxgears
description: Test OpenGL rendering. See also: `vkcube`. More information: <https://manned.org/glxgears>.

name: gmake
description: This command is an alias of GNU `make`.

name: gmd5sum
description: This command is an alias of GNU `md5sum`.

name: gmkdir
description: This command is an alias of GNU `mkdir`.

name: gmkfifo
description: This command is an alias of GNU `mkfifo`.

name: gmknod
description: This command is an alias of GNU `mknod`.

name: gmktemp
description: This command is an alias of GNU `mktemp`.

name: gml2gv
description: Convert a graph from `gml` to `gv` format. Converters: `gml2gv`, `gv2gml`, `gv2gxl`, `gxl2gv`, `graphml2gv` & `mm2gv`. More information: <https://graphviz.org/pdf/gml2gv.1.pdf>.

name: gmssl
description: GmSSL is a crypto toolkit supporting SM1, SM2, SM3, SM4, SM9, and ZUC/ZUC256. More information: <http://gmssl.org/english.html>.

name: gmv
description: This command is an alias of GNU `mv`.

name: gnatmake

name: jira-browse
description: This command is an alias of `jira open`.

name: jira-issue
description: Manage issues in a Jira project. More information: <https://github.com/ankitpokhrel/jira-cli#issue>.

name: jira-issues
description: This command is an alias of `jira issue`.

name: jira-me
description: Display the configured `jira` user. More information: <https://github.com/ankitpokhrel/jira-cli#commands>.

name: jira-navigate
description: This command is an alias of `jira open`.

name: jira-open
description: Open a Jira issue or project in the browser. More information: <https://github.com/ankitpokhrel/jira-cli#other-commands>.

name: jira-project
description: Manage Jira projects. More information: <https://github.com/ankitpokhrel/jira-cli#other-commands>.

name: jira-projects
description: This command is an alias of `jira project`.

name: jira-sprint
description: Manage sprints in a Jira project board. More information: <https://github.com/ankitpokhrel/jira-cli#sprint>.

name: jira-sprints
description: This command is an alias of `jira sprint`.

name: jj
description: Jujutsu, a version control system. Some subcommands such as `log`, `desc`, `new`, `git`, etc. have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://docs.jj-vcs.dev/latest/cli-reference/>.

name: jj-abandon
description: Abandon a revision, rebasing descendants onto its parent(s). Abandoning a revision removes its associated change ID. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-abandon>.

name: jj-absorb
description: Split changes in the source revision and move each change to the closest mutable ancestor where the corresponding lines were modified last. Changes that have zero or multiple matching regions in ancestral revisions won't be moved. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-absorb>.

name: jj-bookmark
description: Manage bookmarks in a `jj` repository. When using a Git backend, bookmarks correspond to Git branches. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-bookmark>.

name: jj-commit
description: Update the description and create a new change on top. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-commit>.

name: jj-describe
description: Update the change description or other metadata. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-describe>.

name: jj-diff
description: Compare file contents between two revisions. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-diff>.

name: jj-diffedit
description: Touch up the content changes in a revision with a diff editor. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-diffedit>.

name: jj-duplicate
description: Create new changes with the same content as existing ones. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-duplicate>.

name: jj-edit
description: Set the specified revision as the working-copy revision. Note: It is generally recommended to instead use `jj new` and `jj squash`. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-edit>.

name: jj-evolog
description: Show how a change has evolved over time, listing the previous commits it has pointed to. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-evolog>.

name: jj-git
description: Run Git-related commands for a `jj` repository. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-git>.

name: jj-git-clone
description: Create a new repo backed by a clone of a Git repo. Note: Unless `--colocate` is used, it is not a valid Git repository and `git` commands can't be used on it. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-git-clone>.

name: jj-git-fetch
description: Fetch from a Git remote, downloading objects and refs from the remote repository. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-git-fetch>.

name: jj-git-init
description: Create a new Git backed Jujutsu repo. Note: Unless `--colocate` is used, it is not a valid Git repository and `git` commands can't be used on it. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-git-init>.

name: jj-git-push
description: Push to a Git remote. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-git-push>.

name: jj-git-remote
description: Manage Git remotes. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-git-remote>.

name: jj-interdiff
description: Compare changes of two revisions. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-interdiff>.

name: jj-log
description: Show revision history as a graph. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-log>.

name: jj-new
description: Create a new empty change. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-new>.

name: jj-next
description: Move the working-copy commit to a child revision. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-next>.

name: jj-operation
description: Work with the operation log of a `jj` repository. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-operation>.

name: jj-parallelize
description: Parallelize revisions by making them siblings. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-parallelize>.

name: jj-prev
description: Move the working-copy commit to a parent revision. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-prev>.

name: jj-rebase
description: Move revisions to different parent(s). More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-rebase>.

name: jj-resolve
description: Resolve conflicted files with an external merge tool. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-resolve>.

name: jj-restore
description: Restore files from another revision. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-restore>.

name: jj-revert
description: Apply the reverse of the given revision(s). More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-revert>.

name: jj-show
description: Show commit description and changes in a revision. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-show>.

name: jj-simplify-parents
description: Simplify parent edges for the specified revision(s). For example, "A -> B -> C | A -> C" gets simplified to "A -> B -> C". More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-simplify-parents>.

name: jj-split
description: Split a revision in two. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-split>.

name: jj-squash
description: Move changes from a revision into another revision. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-squash>.

name: jj-status
description: Show high-level repository status. This includes the working copy commit and its parents, and a summary of the changes in the working copy and any existing conflicts in the working copy. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-status>.

name: jj-undo
description: Undo the most recent recorded operation in a `jj` repository. More information: <https://jj-vcs.github.io/jj/latest/cli-reference/#jj-undo>.

name: jmap
description: Java memory map tool. More information: <https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/specs/man/jmap.html>.

name: jmeter
description: Open source Java application designed for load testing functional behavior and measure performance. More information: <https://jmeter.apache.org/usermanual/get-started.html#options>.

name: jmtpfs
description: FUSE-based filesystem for accessing MTP devices. More information: <https://manned.org/jmtpfs>.

name: jo
description: This command is an alias of `autojump`.

name: jobs
description: Display status of jobs in the current session. More information: <https://manned.org/jobs>.

name: joe
description: Joe's own text editor. More information: <https://joe-editor.sourceforge.io/4.6/man.html>.

name: john
description: Password cracker. More information: <https://www.openwall.com/john/>.

name: join
description: Join lines of two sorted files on a common field. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/join-invocation.html>.

name: josm
description: Extensible OpenStreetMap editor for Java 8+. More information: <https://manned.org/josm>.

name: journalctl
description: Query the systemd journal. See also: `dmesg`. More information: <https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/latest/journalctl.html>.

name: jp2a

name: jpegoptim

name: jpegtopnm

name: jpegtran
description: Perform lossless transformation of JPEG files. More information: <https://manned.org/jpegtran>.

name: jps

name: jq
description: A JSON processor that uses a domain-specific language (DSL). More information: <https://jqlang.org/manual/>.

name: jrnl
description: A simple journal application. More information: <https://jrnl.sh/en/stable/reference-command-line/>.

name: json5

name: jstack

name: jtbl

name: julia

name: jupyter
description: Web application to create and share documents that contain code, visualizations, and notes. Primarily used for data analysis, scientific computing, and machine learning. More information: <https://docs.jupyter.org/en/latest/>.

name: jupyter-lab
description: Interactive development environment for Jupyter notebooks. More information: <https://jupyterlab.readthedocs.io/en/stable/>.

name: jupyterlab

name: jupytext

name: jwt

Data can be selected and simultaneously edited in different locations, using multiple selections; users can also connect to the same session for collaborative editing. More information: <https://manned.org/kak>.

name: katana
description: A fast crawler focused on execution in automation pipelines offering both headless and non-headless crawling. See also: `gau`, `scrapy`, `waymore`. More information: <https://docs.projectdiscovery.io/opensource/katana/usage>.

name: kate
description: KDE's advanced text editor. More information: <https://docs.kde.org/stable/en/kate/kate/fundamentals.html#starting-from-the-command-line>.

name: kcadm.sh
description: Perform administration tasks. More information: <https://www.keycloak.org/docs/latest/server_admin/#admin-cli>.

name: kcat
description: Apache Kafka producer and consumer tool. More information: <https://manned.org/kcat>.

name: kdash
description: A simple dashboard for Kubernetes. More information: <https://github.com/kdash-rs/kdash/#usage>.

name: kde-builder

name: kde-inhibit

name: kdeconnect-cli
description: Use KDE Connect for sharing files or text to a device, ringing it, unlocking it, and much more. More information: <https://manned.org/kdeconnect-cli>.

name: kdenlive
description: KDE's non-linear video editor. More information: <https://manned.org/kdenlive>.

name: kdesrc-build
description: Easily build KDE components from its source repositories. More information: <https://docs.kde.org/trunk5/en/kdesrc-build/kdesrc-build/index.html>.

name: kdialog
description: Show KDE dialog boxes from within shell scripts. More information: <https://develop.kde.org/docs/administration/kdialog/>.

name: kdig
description: Advanced DNS lookup utility. More information: <https://www.knot-dns.cz/docs/latest/html/man_kdig.html>.

name: kdocker
description: Easily dock applications to the system tray. More information: <https://github.com/user-none/KDocker>.

name: keep-header
description: Keep first line untouched by a command, passing it directly to `stdout`. More information: <https://github.com/eBay/tsv-utils#keep-header>.

name: keepass2
description: A light-weight password manager. More information: <https://manned.org/keepass2>.

name: keepassxc-cli
description: Interface for KeePassXC. More information: <https://manned.org/keepassxc-cli>.

name: kerl
description: Build and install Erlang/OTP instances with ease. More information: <https://github.com/kerl/kerl>.

name: kernel-install
description: Add and remove kernel and initrd images to and from `/boot`. More information: <https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/latest/kernel-install.html>.

name: kexec
description: Directly reboot into a new kernel. More information: <https://manned.org/kexec>.

name: keybase
description: Key directory that maps social media identities to encryption keys in a publicly auditable manner. More information: <https://book.keybase.io/docs/cli>.

name: keychain
description: Re-use ssh-agent and/or gpg-agent between logins. More information: <https://www.funtoo.org/Keychain>.

name: keyctl
description: Manipulate the Linux kernel keyring. More information: <https://manned.org/keyctl>.

name: keyd
description: Remap keys. More information: <https://manned.org/keyd>.

name: keytool
description: A certificate management utility included with Java. More information: <https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/specs/man/keytool.html>.

name: khal
description: A text-based calendar and scheduling application. More information: <https://lostpackets.de/khal/>.

name: kill
description: Sends a signal to a process, usually related to stopping the process. All signals except for SIGKILL and SIGSTOP can be intercepted by the process to perform a clean exit. More information: <https://manned.org/kill.1posix>.

name: killall
description: Send kill signal to all instances of a process by name (must be exact name). All signals except SIGKILL and SIGSTOP can be intercepted by the process, allowing a clean exit. More information: <https://manned.org/killall>.

name: kind
description: Run local Kubernetes clusters using Docker container "nodes". Designed for testing Kubernetes itself, but may be used for local development or continuous integration. More information: <https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/kind>.

name: kinfocenter
description: KDE information center to show system information. More information: <https://manned.org/kinfocenter>.

name: kinit
description: Authenticate a principal with a Kerberos server to gain and cache a ticket. Note: A Kerberos principal can be either a user, service, or application. More information: <https://web.mit.edu/kerberos/krb5-latest/doc/user/user_commands/kinit.html>.

name: kismet
description: A wireless network and device detector, sniffer, wardriving tool, and WIDS (wireless intrusion detection) framework. More information: <https://www.kismetwireless.net/docs/readme/starting/commandline/>.

name: kite
description: This command is an alias of `kiterunner`.

name: kiterunner
description: A contextual web scanner for discovering API paths and web endpoints using wordlists and kitebuilder schemas. More information: <https://github.com/assetnote/kiterunner#usage>.

name: kiterunner-brute
description: A contextual web scanner for bruteforcing API paths and web endpoints using wordlists. The `brute` subcommand targets one or multiple hosts. More information: <https://github.com/assetnote/kiterunner#usage>.

name: kiterunner-kb
description: A contextual web scanner for manipulating kitebuilder schemas used in API and web endpoint discovery. The `kb` subcommand handles schema compilation, conversion, parsing, and request replay. More information: <https://github.com/assetnote/kiterunner#usage>.

name: kiterunner-scan
description: A contextual web scanner for concurrently scanning API paths and web endpoints using kitebuilder wordlists. The `scan` subcommand targets one or multiple hosts with structured API requests. More information: <https://github.com/assetnote/kiterunner#usage>.

name: kiterunner-wordlist
description: A contextual web scanner for managing wordlists used in API and web endpoint discovery. The `wordlist` subcommand handles listing and saving wordlists in `~/.cache/kiterunner`. More information: <https://github.com/assetnote/kiterunner#usage>.

name: kitex
description: Code generation tool provided by the Go RPC framework Kitex. Kitex accepts both thrift and protobuf IDLs, and supports generating a skeleton of a server side project. More information: <https://www.cloudwego.io/docs/kitex/tutorials/code-gen/code_generation/#generate-code>.

name: kitty

name: kiwi-ng

name: kjv
description: The word of God available right on your desktop. More information: <https://github.com/layeh/kjv#kjv>.

name: kmod

name: kmutil

name: knife
description: Interact with a Chef server from a local Chef repo. More information: <https://docs.chef.io/workstation/knife/>.

name: knock

name: knockd

name: knotc

name: kodi-send

name: locate

description: Create and start a headless Palworld server. More information: <https://docs.palworldgame.com/settings-and-operation/arguments/>.

name: pamac
description: Utility for the GUI package manager pamac. If you can't see the AUR packages, enable it in `/etc/pamac.conf` or in the GUI. More information: <https://wiki.manjaro.org/index.php/Pamac>.

name: pamarith
description: Apply a binary function on two Netpbm images. See also: `pamfunc`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamarith.html>.

name: pambackground
description: Create a mask of the background in a PAM image. See also: `pbmmask`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pambackground.html>.

name: pambrighten

name: pamcomp
description: Overlay two PAM images. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamcomp.html>.

name: pamcrater
description: Create a PAM image of cratered terrain. See also: `pamshadedrelief`, `ppmrelief`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamcrater.html>.

name: pamcut
description: Cut out a rectangular region from a Netpbm image. See also: `pamdice`, `pamcomp`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamcut.html>.

name: pamdeinterlace
description: Remove every other row in a Netpbm image. See also: `pammixinterlace`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamdeinterlace.html>.

name: pamdepth
description: Reduce the depth (i.e. color resolution) in an image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamdepth.html>.

name: pamdice

name: pamditherbw
description: Apply dithering to a greyscale image, i.e. turn it into a pattern of black and white pixels that look the same as the original greyscale. See also: `pbmreduce`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamditherbw.html>.

name: pamedge
description: Perform edge-detection on a Netpbm image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamedge.html>.

name: pamenlarge
description: Enlarge a PAM image by duplicating pixels. See also: `pbmreduce`, `pamditherbw`, `pbmpscale`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamenlarge.html>.

name: pamexec
description: Execute a shell command on each image in a Netpbm file. See also: `pamfile`, `pampick`, `pamsplit`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamexec.html>.

name: pamfile
description: Describe Netpbm (PAM or PNM) files. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamfile.html>.

name: pamfix
description: Fix errors in PAM, PBM, PGM, and PPM files. See also: `pamfile`, `pamvalidate`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamfix.html>.

name: pamfixtrunc
description: This command has been superseded by `pamfix -truncate`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamfixtrunc.html>.

name: pamflip
description: Flip or rotate a PAM or PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamflip.html>.

name: pamfunc
description: Apply a simple arithmetic function to a Netpbm image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamfunc.html>.

name: pamixer
description: A simple command-line mixer for PulseAudio. More information: <https://github.com/cdemoulins/pamixer#installation>.

name: pammixinterlace
description: Merge each row in an image with its two neighbours. See also: `pamdeinterlace`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pammixinterlace.html>.

name: pamnoraw
description: This command is an alias of `pamtopnm -plain`.

name: pamoil
description: Turn a PAM image into an oil painting. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamoil.html>.

name: pampick
description: Pick images out of a multi-image Netpbm stream. See also: `pamfile`, `pamsplit`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pampick.html>.

name: pampop9
description: Simulate a multi-lens camera such as the Pop9. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pampop9.html>.

name: pamrgbatopng
description: This command has been superseded by `pamtopng`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamrgbatopng.html>.

name: pamscale
description: Scale a Netpbm image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamscale.html>.

name: pamshadedrelief
description: Generate a shaded relief from an elevation map. See also: `pamcrater`, `ppmrelief`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamshadedrelief.html>.

name: pamslice
description: Extract one line of values out of a PAM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamslice.html>.

name: pamsplit
description: Split a multi-image Netpbm file into multiple single-image Netpbm files. See also: `pamfile`, `pampick`, `pamexec`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamsplit.html>.

name: pamstack

name: pamstretch

name: pamtogif

name: pamtopam

name: pamtopng
description: Convert a PAM image to PNG. See also: `pnmtopng`, `pngtopam`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamtopng.html>.

name: pamtopnm

name: pamtoqoi
description: Convert a Netpbm image to a QOI image (Quite OK Image format). More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamtoqoi.html>.

name: pamtosrf

name: pamtotiff

name: pamtouil

name: pamtowinicon
description: Convert a PAM image to a Windows ICO file. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamtowinicon.html>.

name: pamtoxvmini
description: Convert a Netpbm image to an XV thumbnail picture. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamtoxvmini.html>.

name: pamundice
description: Combine a grid of Netpbm images into one. See also: `pamdice`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamundice.html>.

name: pamvalidate
description: Validate PAM, PGM, PBM, and PPM files. See also: `pamfile`, `pamfix`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pamvalidate.html>.

name: pandoc
description: Convert documents between various formats. More information: <https://pandoc.org/MANUAL.html>.

name: pangolin

name: pants
description: Fast, scalable, user-friendly, open-source build and developer workflow tool. More information: <https://www.pantsbuild.org/stable/docs/using-pants/command-line-help>.

name: paperkey
description: An OpenPGP key archiver. More information: <https://www.jabberwocky.com/software/paperkey/>.

name: papermc
description: Manage a Minecraft server. More information: <https://github.com/Edenhofer/minecraft-server/blob/main/minecraftd.sh.in#L480>.

name: parted.interactive
description: A partition manipulation program. See also: `parted`, `partprobe`. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/parted/parted.html>.

name: particle
description: Interact with Particle devices. More information: <https://docs.particle.io/tutorials/developer-tools/cli/>.

name: paste

name: pastel

name: pathchk
description: Check the validity and portability of pathnames. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/pathchk-invocation.html>.

name: pbmtocmuwm

name: pbmtoepsi

name: pbmtoepson

name: pbmtoescp2

name: pbmtoptx

name: pbmtosunicon

name: pbmtoybm

description: Resize container storage. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/pct.1.html#cli_pct_resize>.
