description: Developer Workflow and Environment Management for projects. More information: <https://pixi.prefix.dev/latest/getting_started/>.

name: pixi-config
description: Manage the configuration file. More information: <https://pixi.sh/latest/reference/cli/#config>.

name: pixi-global
description: Manage global packages. More information: <https://pixi.sh/latest/reference/cli/#global>.

name: pixi-project
description: Modify the project configuration file. More information: <https://pixi.sh/latest/reference/cli/#project>.

name: pixi-task
description: Manage tasks in the project environment. More information: <https://pixi.sh/latest/reference/cli/#task>.

name: pixiecore
description: Manage the network booting of machines. More information: <https://github.com/danderson/netboot/tree/main/pixiecore>.

name: pixterm
description: Image printing in the terminal. See also: `chafa`, `catimg`. More information: <https://github.com/eliukblau/pixterm#cool-screenshots>.

name: pjtoppm
description: Convert a HP PaintJet file to PPM. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pjtoppm.html>.

name: pkcon
description: PackageKit client used by Discover and Gnome software and alternative to `apt`. More information: <https://manned.org/pkcon>.

name: pkcs11-tool
description: Utility for managing and using PKCS #11 security tokens. More information: <https://github.com/OpenSC/OpenSC/wiki/Using-pkcs11-tool-and-OpenSSL>.

name: pkexec
description: Execute commands as another user. Asks for password in a GUI if available. See also: `sudo`, `run0`, `doas`. More information: <https://polkit.pages.freedesktop.org/polkit/pkexec.1.html>.

name: pkg
description: Package management utility for Termux. More information: <https://wiki.termux.com/wiki/Package_Management>.

name: pkg_add
description: Install/update packages in OpenBSD. See also: `pkg_info`, `pkg_delete`. More information: <https://man.openbsd.org/pkg_add>.

name: pkg_delete
description: Remove packages in OpenBSD. See also: `pkg_add`, `pkg_info`. More information: <https://man.openbsd.org/pkg_delete>.

name: pkg_info
description: View information about packages in OpenBSD. See also: `pkg_add`, `pkg_delete`. More information: <https://man.openbsd.org/pkg_info>.

name: pkg-config
description: Provide the details of installed libraries for compiling applications. More information: <https://manned.org/pkg-config>.

name: pkgadd
description: Add a package to a CRUX system. More information: <https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E88353_01/html/E72487/pkgadd-8.html>.

name: pkgctl
description: Unified frontend for Arch Linux devtools. More information: <https://manned.org/pkgctl>.

name: pkgctl-auth
description: Authenticate `pkgctl` with services like GitLab. More information: <https://manned.org/pkgctl-auth>.

name: pkgctl-build
description: Build packages inside a clean `chroot`. More information: <https://manned.org/pkgctl-build>.

name: pkgctl-db-update
description: Update the `pacman` database as final release step for packages that have been transferred and staged on <https://repos.archlinux.org>. More information: <https://manned.org/pkgctl-db-update>.

name: pkgctl-diff
description: Compare package files using different modes. See also: `pkgctl`. More information: <https://manned.org/pkgctl-diff>.

name: pkgctl-release
description: Release step to commit, tag, and upload build artifacts. More information: <https://manned.org/pkgctl-release>.

name: pkgctl-repo
description: Manage Git packaging repositories and their configuration for Arch Linux. See also: `pkgctl`. More information: <https://manned.org/pkgctl-repo>.

name: pkgdiff
description: Compare the file contents of two Slackware packages. More information: <https://slackware.nl/slackware/slackware64-current/source/a/pkgtools/manpages/pkgdiff.8>.

name: pkgfile
description: Search files from packages in the official repositories on Arch-based systems. See also: `pacman files` describing the usage of `pacman --files`. More information: <https://manned.org/pkgfile>.

name: pkgin
description: Manage `pkgsrc` binary packages on NetBSD. More information: <https://pkgin.net/#usage>.

name: pkginfo
description: Query the package database on a CRUX system. More information: <https://crux.nu/Main/Handbook3-6#ntoc19>.

name: pkgmk
description: Make a binary package for use with pkgadd on CRUX. More information: <https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E88353_01/html/E37839/pkgmk-1.html>.

name: pkgrm
description: Remove a package from a CRUX system. More information: <https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E88353_01/html/E72487/pkgrm-8.html>.

name: pkgstats
description: Submit and view Arch Linux package popularity statistics. More information: <https://github.com/archlinux-de/pkgstats-cli#usage>.

name: pkgtool
description: Interactive menu-driven tool for managing Slackware packages. See also: `installpkg`, `removepkg`, `upgradepkg`, `makepkg`. More information: <https://www.slackbook.org/html/book.html#PACKAGE-MANAGEMENT-PACKAGE-UTILITIES-PKGTOOL>.

name: pkgutil
description: Query and manipulate Mac OS X Installer packages and receipts. More information: <https://keith.github.io/xcode-man-pages/pkgutil.1.html>.

name: pkgz
description: Unified package manager for multiple sources. More information: <https://github.com/roguehashrate/pkgz#-usage>.

name: pkill
description: Signal process by name. Mostly used for stopping processes. More information: <https://manned.org/pkill>.

name: pkl
description: Manages, evaluates, and tests Pkl configuration modules. More information: <https://pkl-lang.org/main/current/pkl-cli/>.

name: plantuml
description: Create UML diagrams from a plain text language and render them in different formats. More information: <https://plantuml.com/en/command-line>.

name: plasma-apply-colorscheme
description: Switch Plasma color scheme. More information: <https://invent.kde.org/plasma/plasma-workspace>.

name: plasma-apply-cursortheme
description: Switch Plasma cursor theme. More information: <https://invent.kde.org/plasma/plasma-workspace>.

name: plasma-apply-desktoptheme
description: Switch Plasma desktop theme. More information: <https://invent.kde.org/plasma/plasma-workspace>.

name: plasma-apply-lookandfeel
description: Switch Plasma global themes. More information: <https://userbase.kde.org/System_Settings/Look_And_Feel>.

name: plasma-apply-wallpaperimage
description: Switch Plasma wallpaper. More information: <https://invent.kde.org/plasma/plasma-workspace>.

name: plasmashell
description: Start and restart Plasma Desktop. More information: <https://invent.kde.org/plasma/plasma-desktop>.

name: platformio
description: This command is an alias of `pio`.

name: play
description: Audio player of SoX - Sound eXchange. Plays any audio, with audio formats identified by the extension. More information: <https://manned.org/play>.

name: playerctl
description: Control media players via MPRIS. More information: <https://github.com/altdesktop/playerctl#using-the-cli>.

name: plenv
description: Switch between multiple versions of Perl. More information: <https://github.com/tokuhirom/plenv#name>.

name: plesk
description: Plesk hosting control panel. More information: <https://docs.plesk.com/en-US/obsidian/cli-linux/plesk-utility.75661/>.

name: plink
description: PuTTy's command line utility. See also: `ssh`. More information: <https://manned.org/plink>.

name: plocate
description: Find filenames quickly. Make sure to run `sudo updatedb` to include new files. More information: <https://plocate.sesse.net/plocate.1.html>.

name: pluma
description: Edit files in MATE desktop environment. More information: <https://manned.org/pluma>.

name: plutil
description: View, convert, validate, or edit property list ("plist") files. More information: <https://keith.github.io/xcode-man-pages/plutil.1.html>.

name: pm
description: Display information about apps on an Android device. More information: <https://developer.android.com/tools/adb#pm>.

name: pm2
description: Process manager for Node.js. Used for log management, monitoring, and configuring processes. More information: <https://pm2.keymetrics.io/docs/usage/quick-start/>.

name: pmap
description: Report memory map of a process or processes. More information: <https://manned.org/pmap>.

name: pmount
description: Mount arbitrary hotpluggable devices as a normal user. More information: <https://manned.org/pmount>.

name: pmset
description: Configure macOS power management settings, as one might do in System Preferences > Energy Saver. Commands that modify settings must begin with `sudo`. More information: <https://keith.github.io/xcode-man-pages/pmset.1.html>.

name: pngcheck
description: Forensics tool for validating the integrity of PNG based (PNG, JNG, MNG) image files. Can also extract embedded images and text from a file. More information: <https://manned.org/pngcheck>.

name: pngcrush
description: PNG compression utility. More information: <https://pmt.sourceforge.io/pngcrush/>.

name: pngquant
description: PNG converter and lossy image compressor. More information: <https://manned.org/pngquant>.

name: pngtopam
description: Convert a PNG image to a Netpbm image. See also: `pamtopng`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pngtopam.html>.

name: pngtopnm
description: This command has been superseded by `pngtopam`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pngtopnm.html>.

name: pnmalias
description: Apply antialiasing onto a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmalias.html>.

name: pnmarith
description: This command has been superseded by `pamarith`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmarith.html>.

name: pnmcolormap
description: Create quantization color map for a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmcolormap.html>.

name: pnmcomp
description: This command has been superseded by `pamcomp`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmcomp.html>.

name: pnmconvol
description: Convolute a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmconvol.html>.

name: pnmcrop
description: Crop PNM images. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmcrop.html>.

name: pnmcut
description: This command has been superseded by `pamcut`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmcut.html>.

name: pnmdepth
description: This command is an alias of `pamdepth`.

name: pnmenlarge
description: This command has been superseded by `pamenlarge`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmenlarge.html>.

name: pnmfile
description: This command has been superseded by `pamfile`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmfile.html>.

name: pnmflip
description: This command has been superseded by `pamflip`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmflip.html>.

name: pnmgamma
description: Perform gamma correction on PNM images. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmgamma.html>.

name: pnmhisteq
description: Histogram-equalize a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmhisteq.html>.

name: pnmhistmap
description: Draw a histogram of a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmhistmap.html>.

name: pnmindex
description: Build a visual index of multiple PNM images. See also: `pamundice`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmindex.html>.

name: pnminterp
description: This command has been superseded by `pamstretch`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnminterp.html>.

name: pnminvert
description: Invert a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnminvert.html>.

name: pnmmargin
description: Add a border to a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmmargin.html>.

name: pnmmercator
description: Perform Mercator transformations on Netpbm images. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmmercator.html>.

name: pnmmontage
description: Create a montage from multiple PNM images. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmmontage.html>.

name: pnmnlfilt
description: Apply a non-linear filter onto a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmnlfilt.html>.

name: pnmnorm
description: Normalize the contrast in a PNM image. See also: `pnmhisteq`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmnorm.html>.

name: pnmpad
description: Add borders to a PNM image. See also: `pnmmargin`, `pamcut`, `pamcomp`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmpad.html>.

name: pnmpaste
description: Paste a PNM image into another PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmpaste.html>.

name: pnmpsnr
description: Compute the difference between two images. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmpsnr.html>.

name: pnmquant
description: Quantize the colors in a PNM image into a smaller set. This command is a combination of `pnmcolormap` and `pnmremap` and accepts the union of their options, except `-mapfile`. See also: `pnmquantall`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmquant.html>.

name: pnmquantall
description: Run `pnmquant` on multiple files at once such that they share a common colormap. See also: `pnmquant`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmquantall.html>.

name: pnmremap
description: Replace the colors in a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmremap.html>.

name: pnmrotate
description: Rotate a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmrotate.html>.

name: pnmscale
description: This command has been replaced by `pamscale`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmscale.html>.

name: pnmscalefixed
description: Scale a PNM file quickly with possibly reduced quality. See also: `pamscale`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmscalefixed.html>.

name: pnmshear
description: Shear a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmshear.html>.

name: pnmsmooth
description: Smooth out a PNM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmsmooth.html>.

name: pnmsplit
description: This command has been superseded by `pamsplit`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmsplit.html>.

name: pnmtile
description: Replicate an image to fill a specified area. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtile.html>.

name: pnmtoddif
description: Convert a PNM image to a DDIF image file. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtoddif.html>.

name: pnmtofiasco
description: Convert a PNM image to a compressed FIASCO file. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtofiasco.html>.

name: pnmtofits
description: This command has been superseded by `pamtofits`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtofits.html>.

name: pnmtojpeg
description: Convert a PNM image file to the JPEG/JFIF/EXIF image format. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtojpeg.html>.

name: pnmtopalm
description: Convert a PNM image to a Palm bitmap. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtopalm.html>.

name: pnmtopclxl
description: Convert a PNM file to an HP LaserJet PCL XL printer stream. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtopclxl.html>.

name: pnmtoplainpnm
description: This command is an alias of `pamtopnm -plain`.

name: pnmtopng
description: Convert a PNM image file to PNG image format. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtopng.html>.

name: pnmtopnm
description: This command is an alias of `pamtopnm`.

name: pnmtops
description: Convert a PNM image to a PostScript file. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtops.html>.

name: pnmtorast
description: Convert a PNM file to a Sun rasterfile. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtorast.html>.

name: pnmtorle
description: Convert a PNM file to an Utah Raster Tools RLE image file. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtorle.html>.

name: pnmtosgi
description: Convert a PNM file to an SGI image file. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtosgi.html>.

name: pnmtosir
description: Convert a PNM file to a Solitaire Image Recorder file. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtosir.html>.

name: pnmtotiff
description: This command has been superseded by `pamtotiff`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtotiff.html>.

name: pnmtotiffcmyk
description: Convert a PNM image to a CMYK encoded TIFF. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtotiffcmyk.html>.

name: pnmtoxwd
description: Convert a PNM file into an X11 window dump file. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/pnmtoxwd.html>.

name: pnpm
description: Fast, disk space efficient package manager for Node.js. Manage Node.js projects and their module dependencies. More information: <https://pnpm.io/pnpm-cli>.

name: pnpm-audit
description: Scan project dependencies. Check for known security issues with the installed packages. More information: <https://pnpm.io/cli/audit>.

name: pnpm-outdated
description: Check for outdated packages. The check can be limited to a subset of the installed packages by providing arguments (patterns are supported). More information: <https://pnpm.io/cli/outdated>.

name: pnputil
description: Manage the driver store and driver packages on Windows. Requires an elevated Command Prompt. More information: <https://learn.microsoft.com/windows-hardware/drivers/devtest/pnputil-command-syntax>.

name: pnpx
description: Directly execute binaries from npm packages, using `pnpm` instead of `npm`. Note: This command is deprecated! Use `pnpm exec` and `pnpm dlx` instead. More information: <https://cuyl.github.io/pnpm.github.io/pnpx-cli/>.

name: po4a
description: Update both PO files and translated documents. More information: <https://www.po4a.org/man/man1/po4a.1.php>.

name: po4a-gettextize
description: Convert a file to a PO file. More information: <https://www.po4a.org/man/man1/po4a-gettextize.1.php>.

name: po4a-translate
description: Convert a PO file back to documentation format. The provided PO file should be the translation of the POT file which was produced by `po4a-gettextize`. More information: <https://www.po4a.org/man/man1/po4a-translate.1.php>.

name: po4a-updatepo
description: Update the translation (in PO format) of a documentation. More information: <https://www.po4a.org/man/man1/po4a-updatepo.1.php>.

name: pocount
description: Translate Toolkit utility to get translation progress from file, supporting several formats. More information: <https://docs.translatehouse.org/projects/translate-toolkit/en/latest/commands/pocount.html>.

name: pod
description: Dependency manager for Swift and Objective-C Cocoa projects. More information: <https://guides.cocoapods.org/terminal/commands.html>.

name: podman
description: Simple management tool for pods, containers, and images. Podman provides a Docker-CLI comparable command-line. Simply put: `alias docker=podman`. More information: <https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/commands-demo.md>.

name: podman-build
description: Daemonless tool for building container images. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-build.1.html>.

name: podman-compose
description: Run and manage Compose Specification container definition. More information: <https://github.com/containers/podman-compose>.

name: podman-export
description: Export the filesystem of a container and save it as a tarball on the local machine. See also: `podman import`, `podman save`. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-export.1.html>.

name: podman-image
description: Manage OCI/Docker container images. See also: `podman build`, `podman import`. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-image.1.html>.

name: podman-image-load
description: This command is an alias of `podman load`.

name: podman-images
description: Manage OCI/Docker container images. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-images.1.html>.

name: podman-import
description: Import a tarball and save it as a filesystem image. See also: `podman export`, `podman save`. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-import.1.html>.

name: podman-load
description: Load an image from an oci-archive or a docker-archive created using podman save. See also: `podman save`, `podman import`. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-load.1.html>.

name: podman-login
description: Log in to a container registry. Note: The default authfile path on Linux is `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/containers/auth.json`, which is usually stored in a `tmpfs` (in RAM). More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-login.1.html>.

name: podman-machine
description: Create and manage virtual machines running Podman. Included with Podman version 4 or greater. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-machine.1.html>.

name: podman-ps
description: List Podman containers. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-ps.1.html>.

name: podman-rmi
description: Remove OCI/Docker images. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-rmi.1.html>.

name: podman-run
description: Run a command in a new Podman container. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-run.1.html>.

name: podman-save
description: Save an image to a local file or directory. See also: `podman load`, `podman export`. More information: <https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-save.1.html>.

name: poetry
description: Manage Python packages and dependencies. Some subcommands such as `about`, `check`, `env`, etc. have their own usage documentation. See also: `asdf`, `pipenv`, `hatch`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/>.

name: poetry-about
description: Get information about Poetry, an application to manage Python packages and dependencies. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#about>.

name: poetry-add
description: Add required packages to the `pyproject.toml` file in Poetry. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#add>.

name: poetry-build
description: Build a Poetry package as a tarball and a wheel. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#build>.

name: poetry-cache
description: Manage Poetry's cache. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#cache>.

name: poetry-check
description: Manage Poetry file validation and consistency. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#check>.

name: poetry-config
description: Edit poetry config settings and repositories. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#config>.

name: poetry-debug
description: Debug issues with your Poetry project. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#debug>.

name: poetry-env
description: Manage virtual environments associated with a Poetry project. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#env>.

name: poetry-export
description: Export Poetry's lock file to other formats. Provided by the Export Poetry Plugin. More information: <https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry-plugin-export#usage>.

name: poetry-help
description: Display global help, or help for a specific `poetry` command. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#help>.

name: poetry-init
description: Create a basic `pyproject.toml` file interactively. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#init>.

name: poetry-install
description: Install all dependencies for a Python project as defined in the pyproject.toml file. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#install>.

name: poetry-list
description: List available Poetry commands. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#list>.

name: poetry-lock
description: Lock dependencies in `pyproject.toml` (without installing them). See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#lock>.

name: poetry-new
description: Create a new Poetry project in a specific directory. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#new>.

name: poetry-publish
description: Publishes a package to a remote repository. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#publish>.

name: poetry-python
description: Manage Python versions through Poetry. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#python>.

name: poetry-remove
description: Remove a package from the project dependencies. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#remove>.

name: poetry-run
description: Run a command in the project's virtual environment. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#run>.

name: poetry-search
description: Search for packages on a remote index. Note: PyPI no longer supports searching via the command-line, so this command may fail on the default repository. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#search>.

name: poetry-self
description: Manage the Poetry installation/runtime environment itself. These commands reference `pyproject.toml` and `poetry.lock` files in your Poetry configuration directory. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#self>.

name: poetry-shell
description: Spawn a shell within the virtual environment. Note: The `shell` command was moved to a plugin: `poetry-plugin-shell`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#shell>.

name: poetry-show
description: Show details of packages in your Poetry project. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#show>.

name: poetry-source
description: Add source configurations to your Poetry project. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#source>.

name: poetry-sync
description: Syncs your project's environment with the `poetry.lock` file. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#sync>.

name: poetry-update
description: Update the dependencies as according to the `pyproject.toml` file. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#update>.

name: poetry-version
description: Manage Poetry project version. Assumes the following project stages: `patch`, `minor`, `major`, `prepatch`, `preminor`, `premajor`, `prerelease`. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://python-poetry.org/docs/cli/#version>.

name: pokeget
description: Display sprites of Pokemon in your terminal. More information: <https://github.com/talwat/pokeget-rs>.

name: pokego
description: Display Pok√©mon sprites in color directly in your terminal. Inspired by Phoney badger's `pokemon-colorscripts` but offers enhanced speed and efficiency. More information: <https://github.com/rubiin/pokego#usage>.

name: polybar
description: A fast and easy-to-use status bar. More information: <https://github.com/polybar/polybar/wiki>.

name: polybar-msg
description: Control `polybar` using inter-process-messaging (IPC). Note: IPC is disabled by default and can be enabled by setting `enable-ipc = true` in the Polybar config. More information: <https://polybar.readthedocs.io/en/stable/user/ipc.html>.

name: pop
description: Send emails from your terminal. More information: <https://github.com/charmbracelet/pop>.

name: popd
description: Remove a directory placed on the directory stack via the pushd shell built-in. See also: `pushd` to place a directory on the stack and `dirs` to display directory stack contents. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#index-popd>.

name: popeye
description: Report potential issues with Kubernetes deployment manifests. More information: <https://github.com/derailed/popeye>.

name: port
description: Package manager for macOS. More information: <https://guide.macports.org/#using.port>.

name: portablectl
description: A systemd utility for managing and deploying portable service images on Linux systems. More information: <https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/latest/portablectl.html>.

name: portageq
description: Query for information about Portage, the Gentoo Linux package manager. Queryable Portage-specific environment variables are listed in `/var/db/repos/gentoo/profiles/info_vars`. More information: <https://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Portageq>.

name: ports
description: Update/list the ports tree on a CRUX system. More information: <https://manned.org/ports>.

name: postconf
description: Postfix configuration utility. This command displays the values of the `main.cf` configuration parameters by default and warns about possible mistyped parameter names. It can also change the `main.cf` configuration parameter values. More information: <https://manned.org/postconf>.

name: postcss
description: Transform styles with JS plugins. More information: <https://github.com/postcss/postcss-cli#usage>.

name: postfix
description: Postfix mail transfer agent (MTA) control program. More information: <https://www.postfix.org/postfix.1.html>.

name: postgres
description: Run the PostgreSQL database server. More information: <https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/app-postgres.html>.

name: powercfg
description: Configure power settings and manage power schemes. More information: <https://learn.microsoft.com/windows-hardware/design/device-experiences/powercfg-command-line-options>.

name: poweroff
description: Power off the system. More information: <https://manned.org/poweroff>.

name: powerprofilesctl
description: Make power profiles handling available over D-Bus. More information: <https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/upower/power-profiles-daemon#how-to-use>.

name: powershell
description: This command may be mistaken as the cross-platform version of PowerShell (formerly known as PowerShell Core), which uses `pwsh` instead of `powershell`. The original `powershell` command in Windows is still available to use the legacy Windows version of PowerShell (version 5.1 and below). More information: <https://learn.microsoft.com/powershell/module/microsoft.powershell.core/about/about_pwsh>.

name: powerstat
description: Measures the power consumption of a computer that has a battery power source or supports the RAPL interface. More information: <https://manned.org/powerstat>.

name: powertop
description: Optimize battery power usage. More information: <https://github.com/fenrus75/powertop>.

name: ppmbrighten

description: Change all pixels of one color in a PPM image to another color. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppmchange.html>.

name: ppmcie
description: Draw a CIE color chart as a PPM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppmcie.html>.

name: ppmcolormask
description: Produce a mask of areas of a certain color in a PPM image. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppmcolormask.html>.

name: ppmdist

name: ppmflash

name: ppmlabel

name: ppmmix

name: ppmnorm

name: ppmntsc
description: Make the RGB colors in a PPM image compatible with NTSC or PAL color systems. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppmntsc.html>.

name: ppmpat
description: Produce a PPM image with a pattern. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppmpat.html>.

name: ppmquant
description: This command has been replaced by `pnmquant` and `pnmremap`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppmquant.html>.

name: ppmquantall
description: This command has been superseded by `pnmquantall`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppmquantall.html>.

name: ppmrainbow

name: ppmrelief

name: ppmtoilbm

name: ppmtojpeg

name: ppmtouil
description: This command has been superseded by `pamtouil`. More information: <https://netpbm.sourceforge.net/doc/ppmtouil.html>.

name: pueue-help
description: Display help for subcommands. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-kill
description: Kill running tasks or whole groups. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-log
description: Display the log output of 1 or more tasks. See also: `pueue status`. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-parallel
description: Set the amount of allowed parallel tasks. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-pause
description: Pause running tasks or groups. See also: `pueue start`. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-remove
description: Remove tasks from the list. Running or paused tasks need to be killed first. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-reset
description: Kill everything and reset. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-restart
description: Restart tasks. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-send
description: Send input to a task. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-shutdown
description: Remotely shut down the daemon. Only use this subcommand if the daemon isn't started by a service manager. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-start
description: Resume operation of tasks or groups of tasks. See also: `pueue pause`. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-stash
description: Stash tasks to prevent them starting automatically. See also: `pueue start`, `pueue enqueue`. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-status
description: Display the current status of all tasks. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pueue-switch
description: Switches the queue position of two enqueued or stashed commands. More information: <https://github.com/Nukesor/pueue#how-to-use-it>.

name: pulseaudio
description: The PulseAudio sound system daemon and manager. More information: <https://manned.org/pulseaudio>.

name: pulseaudio-ctl
description: Control PulseAudio volume. More information: <https://github.com/graysky2/pulseaudio-ctl>.

name: pulumi
description: Define infrastructure on any cloud using familiar programming languages. Some subcommands such as `up` have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/>.

name: pulumi-about
description: Print information about the Pulumi environment. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_about/>.

name: pulumi-cancel
description: Cancel a stack's currently running update, if any. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_cancel/>.

name: pulumi-config
description: Manage configuration of a Pulumi stack. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_config/>.

name: pulumi-console
description: Open a stack in the Pulumi Console (cloud or self-hosted). It gives you instructions to migrate if not available for your backend. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_console/>.

name: pulumi-destroy
description: Destroy all existing resources in a stack. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_destroy/>.

name: pulumi-down
description: This command is an alias of `pulumi destroy`.

name: pulumi-env
description: Manage Pulumi environments. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_env/>.

name: pulumi-gen-completion
description: Generate completion scripts for the Pulumi CLI. Supported shells are Bash, Zsh, fish. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_gen-completion/>.

name: pulumi-import
description: Import resources into an existing stack. Read syntax for your cloud provider: <https://www.pulumi.com/registry/>. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_import/>.

name: pulumi-install
description: Install packages and plugins for the current program or policy pack. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_install/>.

name: pulumi-login
description: Log in to the Pulumi cloud. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_login/>.

name: pulumi-logout
description: Log out of the Pulumi cloud. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_logout/>.

name: pulumi-new
description: Create a new Pulumi project. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_new/>.

name: pulumi-org
description: Manage Pulumi Organization configuration. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_org/>.

name: pulumi-plugin
description: Manage language and resource provider plugins manually. Other commands manage these automatically. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_plugin/>.

name: pulumi-policy
description: Manage resource policies on Pulumi Cloud (Business Critical) or locally (no organization sub-commands). More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_policy/>.

name: pulumi-preview
description: Show a preview of updates to a stack's resources. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_preview/>.

name: pulumi-refresh
description: Refresh the resources in a stack. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_refresh/>.

name: pulumi-schema
description: Check a Pulumi package schema for errors. Schema reference: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/extending-pulumi/schema/>. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_schema/>.

name: pulumi-stack
description: Manage stacks and view stack state. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_stack/>.

name: pulumi-stack-hist
description: This command is an alias of `pulumi stack history`.

name: pulumi-stack-history
description: Display history for a stack. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_stack_history/>.

name: pulumi-state
description: Edit the current stack's state. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_state/>.

name: pulumi-up
description: Create or update the resources in a stack. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_up/>.

name: pulumi-update
description: This command is an alias of `pulumi up`.

name: pulumi-version
description: Display Pulumi's version number. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_version/>.

name: pulumi-whoami
description: Print information about the currently logged in user. More information: <https://www.pulumi.com/docs/iac/cli/commands/pulumi_whoami/>.

name: pup
description: HTML parsing tool. More information: <https://github.com/ericchiang/pup>.

name: puppet
description: Manage and automate the configuration of servers. Puppet uses a declarative language to define system configurations and apply them automatically. Some subcommands, such as `agent` and `apply`, have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppet/blob/main/references/man/overview.md>.

name: puppet-agent
description: Retrieves the client configuration from a Puppet server and applies it to the local host. More information: <https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppet/blob/main/references/man/agent.md>.

name: puppet-apply
description: Apply Puppet manifests locally. More information: <https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppet/blob/main/references/man/apply.md>.

name: pushd
description: Place a directory on a stack so it can be accessed later. See also: `popd` to switch back to original directory and `dirs` to display directory stack contents. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#index-pushd>.

name: putty
description: SSH, Telnet, and Rlogin client for connecting to remote servers. Note: On Linux, the native `ssh` client is often more convenient. PuTTY is more commonly used on Windows. More information: <https://the.earth.li/~sgtatham/putty/latest/htmldoc/Chapter3.html#using-cmdline>.

name: pv
description: Monitor the progress of data through a pipe. More information: <https://manned.org/pv>.

name: pvchange
description: Change attributes of physical volume(s). More information: <https://manned.org/pvchange>.

name: pvck
description: Check and repair LVM metadata on physical volumes. More information: <https://manned.org/pvck>.

name: pvcreate
description: Initialize a disk or partition for use as a physical volume. See also: `lvm`. More information: <https://manned.org/pvcreate>.

name: pvdisplay
description: Display information about Logical Volume Manager (LVM) physical volumes. See also: `lvm`. More information: <https://manned.org/pvdisplay>.

name: pve-firewall
description: Manage Proxmox VE Firewall. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/wiki/Firewall>.

name: pveam
description: Manage LXC container templates. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/pveam.1.html>.

name: pvecm
description: Proxmox VE Cluster Manager. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/pvecm.1.html>.

name: pveperf
description: A benchmarking tool in Proxmox Server. Gather CPU and hard disk performance data for the hard disk. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/pveperf.1.html>.

name: pvesh
description: Interface with the Proxmox VE API. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/pvesh.1.html>.

name: pvesm
description: Manage Proxmox storage. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/pvesm.1.html>.

name: pveum
description: Manage proxmox users. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/pveum.1.html>.

name: pveversion
description: Proxmox VE version info. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/wiki/Command_Line_Tools#Software_version_check>.

name: pvremove
description: Remove LVM labels from physical volume(s). More information: <https://manned.org/pvremove>.

name: pvs
description: Display information about physical volumes. See also: `lvm`. More information: <https://manned.org/pvs>.

name: pvscan
description: List all physical volumes and manage their online status. More information: <https://manned.org/pvscan>.

name: pw-cat
description: Play and record audio files through PipeWire. See also: `wpctl`, `pw-cli`. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-cat_1.html>.

name: pw-cli
description: Manage a PipeWire instance's modules, objects, nodes, devices, links, and much more. See also: `wpctl`. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-cli_1.html>.

name: pw-config
description: List configuration paths and sections that will be used by the PipeWire server and clients. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-config_1.html>.

name: pw-container
description: Run a program in a new security context. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-container_1.html>.

name: pw-dot
description: Create `.dot` files of the PipeWire graph. See also: `dot` for rendering graph. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-dot_1.html>.

name: pw-dump
description: Dump PipeWire's current state as JSON, including the information on nodes, devices, modules, ports, and other objects. See also: `pw-mon`. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-dump_1.html>.

name: pw-jack
description: Run a JACK application with PipeWire. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-jack_1.html>.

name: pw-link
description: Manage links between ports in PipeWire. More information: <https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/pipewire/pipewire/-/wikis/Virtual-Devices>.

name: pw-loopback
description: Create loopback devices in PipeWire. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-loopback_1.html>.

name: pw-metadata
description: Monitor, set, and delete metadata on PipeWire objects. See also: `pipewire`, `pw-mon`, `pw-cli`. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-metadata_1.html>.

name: pw-mididump
description: Dump MIDI messages to `stdout`. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-mididump_1.html>.

name: pw-mon
description: Monitor objects on the PipeWire instance. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-mon_1.html>.

name: pw-play
description: This command is an alias of `pw-cat --playback`.

name: pw-profiler
description: Profile a local or remote instance. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-profiler_1.html>.

name: pw-record
description: This command is an alias of `pw-cat --record`.

name: pw-reserve
description: Reserve a device for PipeWire. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-reserve_1.html>.

name: pw-top
description: View the PipeWire nodes and devices statistics in real-time. See also: `pipewire`, `pw-dump`, `pw-cli`, `pw-profiler`. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-top_1.html>.

name: pw-v4l2
description: Use v4l2 programs within PipeWire. More information: <https://docs.pipewire.org/page_man_pw-v4l2_1.html>.

name: pwd
description: Print the name of current/working directory. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/pwd-invocation.html>.

name: pwdx
description: Print working directory of a process. More information: <https://manned.org/pwdx>.

name: pwgen
description: Generate pronounceable passwords. More information: <https://manned.org/pwgen>.

name: pwlauncher
description: Manage the Windows To Go startup options. More information: <https://learn.microsoft.com/windows-server/administration/windows-commands/pwlauncher>.

name: pwn
description: Exploit Development Library designed for rapid prototyping. More information: <https://docs.pwntools.com/en/stable/commandline.html>.

name: pwqgen
description: Generate a random passphrase. More information: <https://manned.org/pwqgen>.

name: pwsh
description: Shell and scripting language designed especially for system administration. This command refers to PowerShell version 6 and above (also known as PowerShell Core and cross-platform PowerShell). To use the original Windows version (5.1 and below, also known as the legacy Windows PowerShell), use `powershell` instead of `pwsh`. More information: <https://learn.microsoft.com/powershell/module/microsoft.powershell.core/about/about_pwsh>.

name: pwsh-where
description: This command is an alias of `Where-Object`.

name: py
description: Python Launcher for Windows that runs with specified Python version. See also: `python`. More information: <https://docs.python.org/using/windows.html#python-launcher-for-windows>.

name: py-spy
description: A sampling profiler for Python programs. More information: <https://github.com/benfred/py-spy>.

name: pyats
description: A vendor agnostic test automation framework by Cisco Systems, used for network and systems testing. More information: <https://developer.cisco.com/pyats/>.

name: pyats-shell
description: Start a pre-loaded pyATS interactive Python Shell to save time in prototyping. More information: <https://pubhub.devnetcloud.com/media/genie-docs/docs/cli/genie_shell.html>.

name: pyats-version
description: View and upgrade the pyATS installation. More information: <https://developer.cisco.com/pyats/>.

name: pycodestyle
description: Check Python code against PEP 8 style conventions. More information: <https://pycodestyle.pycqa.org/en/latest/intro.html#example-usage-and-output>.

name: pydoc
description: Display offline Python documentation. More information: <https://docs.python.org/library/pydoc.html>.

name: pydocstyle
description: Statically check Python scripts for compliance with Python docstring conventions. More information: <https://www.pydocstyle.org/en/latest/>.

name: pyenv
description: Switch between multiple versions of Python easily. See also: `asdf`. More information: <https://manned.org/pyenv>.

name: pyenv-virtualenv
description: Create virtual environments based on one's installed Python distributions. More information: <https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv-virtualenv>.

name: pyflakes
description: Checks Python source code files for errors. More information: <https://pypi.org/project/pyflakes>.

name: pygbag
description: Package Pygame projects as WebAssembly to run in web browsers. More information: <https://github.com/pygame-web/pygbag#pygbag>.

name: pygmentize
description: Python-based syntax highlighter. More information: <https://pygments.org/docs/cmdline/>.

name: pyinfra
description: Automates infrastructure at a large scale. More information: <https://docs.pyinfra.com/en/3.x/cli.html>.

name: pylint
description: A Python code linter. More information: <https://pylint.pycqa.org/en/latest/>.

name: pypy
description: Fast and compliant alternative implementation of the Python language. More information: <https://manned.org/pypy>.

name: pyrit
description: WPA/WPA2 cracking tool using computational power. More information: <https://manned.org/pyrit>.

name: pystun3
description: Classic STUN client written in Python. More information: <https://github.com/talkiq/pystun3>.

name: pytest
description: Run Python tests. More information: <https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/how-to/usage.html>.

name: python
description: Python language interpreter. More information: <https://docs.python.org/using/cmdline.html>.

name: python-m-json.tool
description: Validate and pretty-print JSON data. Part of Python's standard library. More information: <https://docs.python.org/library/json.html#module-json.tool>.

name: python3
description: This command is an alias of `python`.

name: q
description: Execute SQL-like queries on CSV and TSV files. More information: <https://harelba.github.io/q/>.

name: qalc
description: Powerful and easy to use calculator. See also: `bc`. More information: <https://qalculate.github.io/manual/qalc.html>.

name: qc
description: Manage and execute command snippets stored in QOwnNotes notes. See also: `qownnotes`. More information: <https://www.qownnotes.org/getting-started/command-line-snippet-manager.html>.

name: qcp
description: Copy files using the default text editor to define the filenames. More information: <https://manned.org/qcp>.

name: qdbus
description: Inter-Process Communication (IPC) and Remote Procedure Calling (RPC) mechanism originally developed for Linux. More information: <https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtdbus-index.html>.

name: qemu-img
description: Create and manipulate Quick Emulator Virtual HDD images. More information: <https://qemu.readthedocs.io/en/master/tools/qemu-img.html>.

name: qemu-system-i386
description: Emulate the `i386` architecture. More information: <https://www.qemu.org/docs/master/system/target-i386.html>.

name: qemu-system-riscv64
description: Emulate `riscv64` architecture. More information: <https://www.qemu.org/docs/master/system/target-riscv.html>.

name: qemu-system-x86_64
description: Emulate the `x86_64` architecture. More information: <https://www.qemu.org/docs/master/system/target-i386.html>.

name: qjoypad
description: Translate input from gamepads or joysticks into keyboard strokes or mouse actions. More information: <https://qjoypad.sourceforge.net/doc/doc_index.html>.

name: qlmanage
description: QuickLook server tool. More information: <https://keith.github.io/xcode-man-pages/qlmanage.1.html>.

name: qm
description: QEMU/KVM Virtual Machine Manager. Some subcommands such as `list`, `start`, `stop`, `clone`, etc. have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html>.

name: qm-agent
description: This command is an alias of `qm guest cmd`.

name: qm-cleanup
description: Clean up resources on QEMU/KVM Virtual Machine Manager like tap devices, VGPUs, etc. Called after a VM shuts down, crashes, etc. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_cleanup>.

name: qm-clone
description: Create a copy of virtual machine on QEMU/KVM Virtual Machine Manager. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_clone>.

name: qm-cloudinit
description: Manage Cloud-Init settings. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_cloudinit_dump>.

name: qm-config
description: Display the virtual machine configuration with pending configuration changes applied. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_config>.

name: qm-create
description: Create or restore a virtual machine on QEMU/KVM Virtual Machine Manager. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_create>.

name: qm-delsnapshot
description: Delete virtual machine snapshots. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_delsnapshot>.

name: qm-destroy
description: Destroy a virtual machine in QEMU/KVM Virtual Machine Manager. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_destroy>.

name: qm-disk
description: Manage disk images. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_disk_import>.

name: qm-guest
description: Manage a VM guest agent. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_guest_cmd>.

name: qm-guest-exec
description: Execute a specific command via a guest agent. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_guest_exec>.

name: qm-help
description: Display help for a command. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_help>.

name: qm-importdisk
description: This command is an alias of `qm disk import`.

name: qm-list
description: List all virtual machines. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_list>.

name: qm-listsnapshot
description: List snapshots of virtual machines. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_listsnapshot>.

name: qm-migrate
description: Migrate a virtual machine. Used to create a new migration task. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_migrate>.

name: qm-monitor
description: Enter the QEMU Monitor interface. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_monitor>.

name: qm-move_disk
description: This command is an alias of `qm disk move`.

name: qm-move-disk
description: This command is an alias of `qm disk move`.

name: qm-mtunnel
description: Used by `qmigrate`. It should not be invoked manually. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_mtunnel>.

name: qm-nbdstop
description: Stop embedded nbd server. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_nbdstop>.

name: qm-pending
description: Get the virtual machine configuration with both current and pending values. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_pending>.

name: qm-reboot
description: Reboot a virtual machine by shutting it down, and starting it again after applying pending changes. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_reboot>.

name: qm-rescan
description: This command is an alias of `qm disk rescan`.

name: qm-reset
description: Reset a virtual machine on QEMU/KVM Virtual Machine Manager. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_reset>.

name: qm-resize
description: This command is an alias of `qm disk resize`.

name: qm-resume
description: Resume a virtual machine. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_resume>.

name: qm-rollback
description: Rollback the VM state to a specified snapshot. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_rollback>.

name: qm-sendkey
description: Send QEMU monitor encoding key event to a virtual machine. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_sendkey>.

name: qm-set
description: Set virtual machine options. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_set>.

name: qm-showcmd
description: Show command-line which is used to start the VM (debug info). More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_showcmd>.

name: qm-shutdown
description: Shutdown a virtual machine on QEMU/KVM Virtual Machine Manager. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_shutdown>.

name: qm-snapshot
description: Create virtual machine snapshots. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_snapshot>.

name: qm-start
description: Start a virtual machine on QEMU/KVM Virtual Machine Manager. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_start>.

name: qm-status
description: Show virtual machine status. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_status>.

name: qm-stop
description: Stop a virtual machine. More information: <https://pve.proxmox.com/pve-docs/qm.1.html#cli_qm_stop>.

name: qm-suspend
