name: tsv-filter
description: Filter lines of a TSV file by running tests against individual fields. More information: <https://github.com/eBay/tsv-utils#tsv-filter>.

name: tt
description: A terminal based typing test. More information: <https://github.com/lemnos/tt>.

name: tts
description: Synthesize speech. More information: <https://github.com/coqui-ai/TTS#command-line-tts>.

name: tty
description: Returns terminal name. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/tty-invocation.html>.

name: ttyd
description: Share a terminal or any command over the web. More information: <https://github.com/tsl0922/ttyd#command-line-options>.

name: ttyplot
description: A realtime plotting utility for the command-line with data input from `stdin`. More information: <https://github.com/tenox7/ttyplot>.

name: tuc
description: Cut text (or bytes) where a delimiter matches, then keep the desired parts. A more user-friendly and powerful version of `cut` with sensible defaults. More information: <https://github.com/riquito/tuc#help>.

name: tuckr
description: Dotfile manager written in Rust. See also: `chezmoi`, `vcsh`, `homeshick`, `stow`. More information: <https://github.com/RaphGL/Tuckr#usage>.

name: tuir
description: A text user-interface (TUI) to view and interact with Reddit from your terminal. Navigate with the Vim keys. More information: <https://gitlab.com/ajak/tuir>.

name: tune.exfat
description: Adjust tunable filesystem parameters on an exFAT filesystem. More information: <https://manned.org/tune.exfat>.

name: tune2fs
description: Adjust parameters of an ext2, ext3, or ext4 filesystem. May be used on mounted filesystems. More information: <https://manned.org/tune2fs>.

name: tuned-adm
description: Manage and optimize system performance tuning profiles on Linux. More information: <https://manned.org/tuned-adm>.

name: tunelp
description: Set various parameters for parallel port devices for troubleshooting or for better performance. Part of `util-linux`. More information: <https://manned.org/tunelp>.

name: turbo
description: High-performance build system for JavaScript and TypeScript codebases. See also: `nx`. More information: <https://turborepo.com/docs/reference>.

name: turbostat
description: Report processor topology, frequency, temperature, power, and idle statistics. More information: <https://manned.org/turbostat>.

name: tuxi
description: Scrape Google search results and SERPs and provide instant and concise answers. More information: <https://github.com/Bugswriter/tuxi#usage>.

name: tv
description: Cross-platform, fast, extensible fuzzy-finder tool. Works with "channels" (e.g., files, env, git repos) or from `stdin`. More information: <https://alexpasmantier.github.io/television/>.

name: twine
description: Utility for publishing Python packages on PyPI. More information: <https://twine.readthedocs.io/en/stable/#commands>.

name: twm
description: A window manager for the X Window system. More information: <https://manned.org/twm>.

name: twopi
description: Render an image of a `radial` network graph from a `graphviz` file. Layouts: `dot`, `neato`, `twopi`, `circo`, `fdp`, `sfdp`, `osage` & `patchwork`. More information: <https://graphviz.org/doc/info/command.html>.

name: twurl
description: Curl-like command but tailored specifically for the Twitter API. More information: <https://github.com/twitter/twurl#getting-started>.

name: twurl-accounts
description: Manage and list Twitter accounts authorized with twurl. More information: <https://github.com/twitter/twurl#changing-your-default-profile>.

name: tye
description: Develop, test, and deploy microservices and distributed applications easily. More information: <https://github.com/dotnet/tye>.

name: type
description: Display the type of command the shell will execute. Note: All examples are not POSIX compliant. See also: `whereis`, `which`. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#index-type>.

name: typeinc
description: An `ncurses` based terminal typing speed test program, written in Python. Try out different difficulty levels and improve your typing speed. More information: <https://github.com/AnirudhG07/Typeinc>.

name: typeorm
description: A JavaScript ORM that can run on Node.js, browser, Cordova, Ionic, React Native, NativeScript, and Electron platforms. More information: <https://typeorm.io/docs/advanced-topics/using-cli/#initialize-a-new-typeorm-project>.

name: typeset
description: This command is an alias of `declare`.

name: typst
description: Compile a Typst file to PDF. Note: Specifying the output location is optional. More information: <https://manned.org/typst>.

name: tzconfig
description: Manage and set your local timezone. It accepts no parameters. More information: <https://manned.org/tzconfig>.

name: tzselect
description: Interactively select timezone. Note: This program doesn't actually set the timezone. More information: <https://manned.org/tzselect>.

name: tzutil
description: A tool for displaying or configuring the system time zone. More information: <https://learn.microsoft.com/windows-server/administration/windows-commands/tzutil>.

name: u3d
description: A set of tools to interact with Unity. More information: <https://github.com/DragonBox/u3d>.

name: ubuntu-bug
description: This command is an alias of `apport-bug`.

name: ubuntu-drivers
description: Install drivers on Ubuntu. More information: <https://documentation.ubuntu.com/server/how-to/graphics/install-nvidia-drivers/index.html>.

name: ubuntu-security-status
description: Display information about security support for installed Ubuntu packages. More information: <https://git.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/update-manager/tree/ubuntu-security-status>.

name: ubus
description: Interact with an OpenWrt ubusd server. More information: <https://openwrt.org/docs/techref/ubus>.

name: uci
description: Manage OpenWrt configuration files. More information: <https://openwrt.org/docs/techref/uci>.

name: udevadm
description: Linux `udev` management tool. More information: <https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/latest/udevadm.html>.

name: udevmon
description: Intercept and monitor input devices for launching tasks. Filters or modifies events according to configuration file(s) (default: `/etc/interception/udevmon.d/*.yaml`). More information: <https://gitlab.com/interception/linux/tools/-/tree/master#udevmon>.

name: udiskie
description: A user-level automounter for removable media using udisks2. See also: `udiskie-mount`, `udiskie-umount`. More information: <https://github.com/coldfix/udiskie/wiki/Usage>.

name: udiskie-dmenu
description: A dmenu/rofi-based frontend for udiskie to mount and unmount devices interactively. Requires udiskie and either dmenu or rofi. More information: <https://github.com/fogine/udiskie-dmenu>.

name: udiskie-mount
description: Manually mount devices using udiskie. See also: `udiskie`, `udiskie-umount`. More information: <https://github.com/coldfix/udiskie/wiki/Usage>.

name: udiskie-umount
description: Manually unmount devices using udiskie. See also: `udiskie`, `udiskie-mount`. More information: <https://github.com/coldfix/udiskie/wiki/Usage>.

name: udisksctl
description: Interact with `udisksd` to query and manipulate storage devices. More information: <https://storaged.org/doc/udisks2-api/latest/udisksctl.1.html>.

name: ufraw-batch
description: Convert RAW files from cameras into standard image files. More information: <https://manned.org/ufraw-batch>.

name: ufw
description: Uncomplicated Firewall. Frontend for `iptables` aiming to make configuration of a firewall easier. More information: <https://wiki.ubuntu.com/UncomplicatedFirewall>.

name: ug
description: This command is an alias of `ugrep --config --pretty --sort`.

name: ugrep
description: Ultra fast search tool with query TUI. More information: <https://github.com/Genivia/ugrep#man-page>.

name: uinput
description: Intercept and write input events to a virtual keyboard device using /dev/uinput. More information: <https://gitlab.com/interception/linux/tools/-/tree/master#uinput>.

name: ul
description: Underline a text. Each character in a string must be underlined separately. More information: <https://manned.org/ul>.

name: ulimit
description: Get and set resource limits for user processes. This is a shell builtin hence not shell-agnostic. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#index-ulimit>.

name: umask
description: Manage the read/write/execute permissions that are masked out (i.e. restricted) for newly created files by the user. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#index-umask>.

name: umount
description: Unlink a filesystem from its mount point, making it no longer accessible. A filesystem cannot be unmounted when it is busy. More information: <https://man.openbsd.org/umount>.

name: unalias
description: Remove aliases. See also: `alias`. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#index-unalias>.

name: uname
description: Print details about the current machine and the operating system running on it. See also: `lsb_release`. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/uname-invocation.html>.

name: uname26
description: This command is an alias of `setarch uname26`.

name: unar
description: Extract contents from archive files. More information: <https://manned.org/unar>.

name: unclutter
description: Hides the mouse cursor. More information: <https://manned.org/unclutter.1x>.

name: uncompress
description: Uncompress files compressed using the Unix `compress` command. More information: <https://manned.org/uncompress>.

name: uncrustify
description: C, C++, C#, D, Java, and Pawn source code formatter. More information: <https://manned.org/uncrustify>.

name: unexpand
description: Convert spaces to tabs. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/unexpand-invocation.html>.

name: unflatten
description: Adjust directed graphs to improve the layout aspect ratio. Graphviz filters: `acyclic`, `bcomps`, `comps`, `edgepaint`, `gvcolor`, `gvpack`, `mingle`, `nop`, `sccmap`, `tred`, & `unflatten`. More information: <https://www.graphviz.org/pdf/unflatten.1.pdf>.

name: unimatrix
description: Simulate the Matrix look with Unicode characters. See also: `cmatrix`. More information: <https://github.com/will8211/unimatrix>.

name: uniq
description: Output the unique lines from a input or file. Since it does not detect repeated lines unless they are adjacent, we need to sort them first. See also: `sort`. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/uniq-invocation.html>.

name: unison
description: Bidirectional file synchronisation tool. More information: <https://github.com/bcpierce00/unison>.

name: units
description: Convert between two units of measure. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/units/manual/units.html>.

name: universalaccessd
description: Get universal access services. It should not be invoked manually. More information: <https://keith.github.io/xcode-man-pages/universalaccessd.8.html>.

name: unix2dos
description: Change Unix-style line endings to DOS-style. Replaces LF with CRLF. See also: `unix2mac`, `dos2unix`, `mac2unix`. More information: <https://manned.org/unix2dos>.

name: unix2mac
description: Change Unix-style line endings to macOS-style. Replaces LF with CR. See also: `unix2dos`, `dos2unix`, `mac2unix`. More information: <https://manned.org/unix2mac>.

name: unlink
description: Remove a link to a file from the filesystem. The file contents is lost if the link is the last one to the file. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/unlink-invocation.html>.

name: unlzma
description: This command is an alias of `xz --format lzma --decompress`.

name: unmount
description: The correct command is `umount` (u-mount).

name: unopkg
description: LibreOffice extensions manager. Download extensions from <https://extensions.libreoffice.org>. See also: `libreoffice`. More information: <https://manned.org/unopkg>.

name: unp
description: Extract any archive. Relevant extractors need to be installed, e.g. `unrar` for RAR. More information: <https://manned.org/unp>.

name: unrar
description: Extract RAR archives. More information: <https://manned.org/unrar>.

name: unset
description: Remove shell variables or functions. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#index-unset>.

name: unsetopt
description: Unset options for the Z shell (`zsh`). Note: Zsh options are case-insensitive and underscores are ignored. See also: `setopt` to set options. More information: <https://zsh.sourceforge.io/Doc/Release/Options.html>.

name: unshadow
description: Utility provided by the John the Ripper project to obtain the traditional Unix password file if the system uses shadow passwords. More information: <https://www.openwall.com/john/doc/>.

name: unshare
description: Execute a command in new user-defined namespaces. More information: <https://manned.org/unshare>.

name: unsquashfs
description: Uncompress, extract, and list files in squashfs filesystems. More information: <https://manned.org/unsquashfs>.

name: until
description: Simple shell loop that repeats until it receives zero as return value. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#index-until>.

name: unxz
description: This command is an alias of `xz --decompress`.

name: unzip
description: Extract files/directories from Zip archives. See also: `zip`. More information: <https://manned.org/unzip>.

name: unzipsfx
description: Create a self-extracting compressed binary file by prepending self-extracting stubs on a Zip file. More information: <https://manned.org/unzipsfx>.

name: unzstd
description: This command is an alias of `zstd --decompress`.

name: update-alternatives
description: Convenientily maintain symbolic links to determine default commands. More information: <https://manned.org/update-alternatives>.

name: update-grub
description: This command is an alias of `grub-mkconfig --output /boot/grub/grub.cfg`.

name: update-initramfs
description: Manage initramfs. More information: <https://manned.org/update-initramfs>.

name: update-rc.d
description: Install and remove services which are System-V style init script links. Init scripts are in the `/etc/init.d/`. More information: <https://manned.org/update-rc.d>.

name: updatectl
description: System update utility. More information: <https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/latest/updatectl.html>.

name: updatedb
description: Create or update the database used by `locate`. It is usually run daily by cron. More information: <https://manned.org/updatedb>.

name: updog
description: A replacement for Python's SimpleHTTPServer. It allows uploading and downloading via HTTP/S, can set ad hoc SSL certificates and use HTTP basic auth. More information: <https://github.com/sc0tfree/updog>.

name: updpkgsums
description: Update the checksums of the sources in a `PKGBUILD`. Unless a preexisting hashing algorithm is used, SHA256 will be used. More information: <https://manned.org/updpkgsums>.

name: upgradepkg
description: Upgrade Slackware packages by replacing existing packages with new versions. See also: `installpkg`, `removepkg`, `makepkg`, `pkgtool`. More information: <https://slackware.nl/slackware/slackware64-current/source/a/pkgtools/manpages/upgradepkg.8>.

name: upnpc
description: Configure port forwarding rules on your router via the UPnP protocol. More information: <https://manned.org/upnpc>.

name: upower
description: System utility to provide power and battery information and statistics. More information: <https://upower.freedesktop.org/docs/upower.1.html>.

name: uprecords
description: Display a summary of historical uptime records. More information: <https://manned.org/uprecords>.

name: upt
description: Unified interface for managing packages across various operating systems, like Windows, many Linux distributions, macOS, FreeBSD, and even Haiku. It requires the native OS package manager to be installed. See also: `flatpak`, `brew`, `scoop`, `apt`, `dnf`. More information: <https://github.com/sigoden/upt>.

name: uptime
description: Tell how long the system has been running and other information. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/uptime-invocation.html>.

name: upx
description: Compress or decompress executables. More information: <https://github.com/upx/upx/blob/devel/doc/upx.pod>.

name: urpme
description: Uninstall packages in Mageia. See also: `urpmi`, `urpmi.update`, `urpmi.addmedia`, `urpmi.removemedia`, `urpmf`, `urpmq`. More information: <https://man.linuxreviews.org/man8/urpme.8.html>.

name: urpmf
description: Find files in packages and query information about them in Mageia. See also: `urpmi`, `urpme`, `urpmi.addmedia`, `urpmi.removemedia`, `urpmi.update`, `urpmq`. More information: <https://man.linuxreviews.org/man8/urpmf.8.html>.

name: urpmi
description: Install packages in Mageia. See also: `urpmi.update`, `urpme`, `urpmi.addmedia`, `urpmi.removemedia`, `urpmf`, `urpmq`. More information: <https://man.linuxreviews.org/man8/urpmi.8.html>.

name: urpmi.addmedia
description: Add media in Mageia. Note: Mageia documentation uses medium and repository as synonymous. See also: `urpmi`, `urpmi.update`, `urpme`, `urpmi.removemedia`, `urpmf`, `urpmq`. More information: <https://man.linuxreviews.org/man8/urpmi.addmedia.8.html>.

name: urpmi.removemedia
description: Remove media in Mageia. Note: Mageia documentation uses medium and repository as synonymous. See also: `urpmi`, `urpme`, `urpmi.addmedia`, `urpmi.update`, `urpmf`, `urpmq`. More information: <https://man.linuxreviews.org/man8/urpmi.removemedia.8.html>.

name: urpmi.update
description: Update the list of packages from a package repository in Mageia. Note: Mageia documentation uses medium and repository as synonymous. See also: `urpmi`, `urpme`, `urpmi.addmedia`, `urpmi.removemedia`, `urpmf`, `urpmq`. More information: <https://man.linuxreviews.org/man8/urpmi.update.8.html>.

name: urpmq
description: Query information about packages and media in Mageia. See also: `urpmi`, `urpmi.update`, `urpmi.addmedia`, `urpmi.removemedia`, `urpmf`, `urpme`. More information: <https://man.linuxreviews.org/man8/urpmq.8.html>.

name: urxvt
description: Rxvt-unicode. A customizable terminal emulator. More information: <https://manned.org/urxvt>.

name: usbip
description: Use USB devices remotely. More information: <https://manned.org/usbip>.

name: useradd
description: Create a new user. See also: `users`, `userdel`, `usermod`. More information: <https://manned.org/useradd>.

name: userdbctl
description: Inspect users, groups, and group memberships on the system. More information: <https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/latest/userdbctl.html>.

name: userdel
description: Remove a user account or remove a user from a group. See also: `users`, `useradd`, `usermod`. More information: <https://manned.org/userdel>.

name: usermod
description: Modify a user account. See also: `users`, `useradd`, `userdel`. More information: <https://manned.org/usermod>.

name: username
description: Manage users. Accessed in configuration mode. More information: <https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/security/s1/sec-s1-xe-3se-3850-cr-book/sec-s1-xe-3se-3850-cr-book_chapter_0110.html>.

name: usernoted
description: Provides notification services. It should not be invoked manually. More information: <https://keith.github.io/xcode-man-pages/usernoted.8.html>.

name: users
description: Display a list of logged in users. See also: `who`, `w`, `useradd`, `userdel`, `usermod`. More information: <https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/html_node/users-invocation.html>.

name: usleep
description: Delay execution for a specific interval in microseconds. Largely deprecated in favor of `nanosleep`. See also: `sleep`. More information: <https://manned.org/usleep.1>.

name: usql
description: Universal CLI interface for SQL databases. More information: <https://github.com/xo/usql#using>.

name: utmpdump
description: Dump and load btmp, utmp, and wtmp accounting files. More information: <https://manned.org/utmpdump>.

name: uudecode
description: Decode files encoded by `uuencode`. More information: <https://manned.org/uudecode>.

name: uuencode
description: Encode binary files into ASCII for transport via mediums that only support simple ASCII encoding. More information: <https://manned.org/uuencode>.

name: uuid
description: Generate and decode Universally Unique Identifiers (UUID). See also: `uuidgen`. More information: <https://manned.org/uuid>.

name: uuidd
description: Daemon for generating UUIDs. More information: <https://manned.org/uuidd>.

name: uuidgen
description: Generate unique identifiers (UUIDs). See also: `uuid`. More information: <https://manned.org/uuidgen>.

name: uuidparse
description: Parse universally unique identifiers. See also: `uuidgen`. More information: <https://manned.org/uuidparse>.

name: uv
description: A fast Python package and project manager. Some subcommands such as `tool` and `python` have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/>.

name: uv-add
description: Add package dependencies to the `pyproject.toml` file. Packages are specified according to <https://peps.python.org/pep-0508/>. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-add>.

name: uv-build
description: Build Python packages into source distributions and wheels. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-build>.

name: uv-cache
description: Manage `uv`'s global cache directory. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-cache>.

name: uv-export
description: Export the project's lockfile to an alternate format. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-export>.

name: uv-help
description: Display detailed documentation for `uv` commands. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-help>.

name: uv-init
description: Create a new Python project. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-init>.

name: uv-lock
description: Update the project's lockfile. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-lock>.

name: uv-pip
description: Provides pip-like commands for installing, uninstalling, and managing packages. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-pip>.

name: uv-publish
description: Upload distributions to an index. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-publish>.

name: uv-python
description: Manage Python versions and installations. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-python>.

name: uv-remove
description: Remove dependencies from the project's `pyproject.toml` file. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-remove>.

name: uv-run
description: Run a command or script in the project environment. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-run>.

name: uv-self
description: Manage the `uv` executable itself. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-self>.

name: uv-sync
description: Update the project's environment to match the lockfile. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-sync>.

name: uv-tool
description: Install and run commands provided by Python packages. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-tool>.

name: uv-tree
description: Display project dependencies in a tree format. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-tree>.

name: uv-venv
description: Create an isolated Python environment for installing packages. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-venv>.

name: uv-version
description: Read or update a project's version. More information: <https://docs.astral.sh/uv/reference/cli/#uv-version>.

name: uvcdynctrl
description: Manage dynamic controls in uvcvideo. More information: <https://manned.org/uvcdynctrl>.

name: uvicorn
description: Python ASGI HTTP Server, for asynchronous projects. More information: <https://www.uvicorn.org/settings/>.

name: uvx
description: This command is an alias of `uv tool run`.

name: uwfmgr
description: Unified Write Filter (UWF). Protect drives by redirecting any writes to the drive to a virtual overlay. Writes are discarded upon reboot unless committed by default. More information: <https://learn.microsoft.com/windows/iot/iot-enterprise/customize/unified-write-filter>.

name: v
description: A tool for managing V source code. More information: <https://docs.vlang.io/getting-started.html>.

name: v4l2-ctl
description: Control video devices. More information: <https://manned.org/v4l2-ctl>.

name: vacuumdb
description: Garbage-collect and analyze a PostgreSQL database. More information: <https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/app-vacuumdb.html>.

name: vagrant
description: Manage lightweight, reproducible, and portable development environments. Some subcommands such as `box`, `snapshot`, `halt`, etc. have their own usage documentation. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli>.

name: vagrant-box
description: Manage Vagrant boxes (virtual machine images). See also: `vagrant`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/box>.

name: vagrant-destroy
description: Stop a guest machine and destroy all its resources. Any boxes installed are kept intact. See also: `vagrant`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/destroy>.

name: vagrant-global-status
description: Display the state of all Vagrant machines on the system. The info is based on a cache, which may become stale and require pruning. See also: `vagrant`, `vagrant status`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/global-status>.

name: vagrant-halt
description: Shuts down the running machine Vagrant is managing. See also: `vagrant`, `vagrant box`, `vagrant plugin`, `vagrant validate`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/halt>.

name: vagrant-init
description: Initialize a Vagrant environment in the current directory by creating a `Vagrantfile`. See also: `vagrant`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/init>.

name: vagrant-plugin
description: Manage Vagrant plugins. See also: `vagrant`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/plugin>.

name: vagrant-port
description: List mappings between guest and host ports. See also: `vagrant`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/port>.

name: vagrant-reload
description: Equivalent of running `halt` followed by `up`. A reload is usually required for changes in a Vagrantfile to take effect. See also: `vagrant`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/reload>.

name: vagrant-resume
description: Resume a Vagrant managed machine that was previously suspended. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/resume>.

name: vagrant-snapshot
description: Manage snapshots of Vagrant machines. See also: `vagrant`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/snapshot>.

name: vagrant-ssh
description: SSH into a running Vagrant machine. See also: `vagrant`. More information: <https://developer.hashicorp.com/vagrant/docs/cli/ssh>.

name: vagrant-ssh-config

description: IRC bouncer. More information: <https://manned.org/znc>.

name: znew
description: Recompress files from `.Z` to gzip format. More information: <https://manned.org/znew>.

name: zola
description: A static site generator in a single binary with everything built-in. More information: <https://www.getzola.org/documentation/getting-started/cli-usage/>.

name: zoneadm
description: Administer Oracle Solaris zones. More information: <https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E88353_01/html/E72487/zoneadm-8.html>.

name: zopflipng
description: PNG compression utility. More information: <https://github.com/google/zopfli>.

name: zotero
description: Manage your bibliographies. More information: <https://www.zotero.org/support/>.

name: zoxide
description: Keep track of the most frequently used directories. Uses a ranking algorithm to navigate to the best match. More information: <https://manned.org/zoxide>.

name: zpaq
description: Incremental journaling backup utility and archiver. More information: <https://mattmahoney.net/dc/zpaqdoc.html>.

name: zpool
description: Manage ZFS pools. More information: <https://manned.org/zpool>.

name: zramctl
description: Setup and control zram devices. Use `mkfs` or `mkswap` to format zram devices to partitions. More information: <https://manned.org/zramctl>.

name: zrok
description: Expose local services and files to the internet. Part of the OpenZiti project, offering secure, zero-trust sharing. More information: <https://docs.zrok.io/>.

name: zrun
description: Transparently uncompress argument files to a command. More information: <https://manned.org/zrun>.

name: zsh
description: Z SHell, a Bash-compatible command-line interpreter. See also: `bash`, `!`, `^`. More information: <https://zsh.sourceforge.io/Doc/Release/Invocation.html#Invocation>.

name: zstd
description: Compress or decompress files with Zstandard compression. More information: <https://manned.org/zstd>.

name: zstdcat
description: This command is an alias of `zstd --decompress --stdout --force`.

name: zstdless
description: Open a `zstd` compressed file for interactive reading, allowing scrolling and search. See also: `zstd`, `less`. More information: <https://manned.org/zstdless>.

name: zstdmt
description: This command is an alias of `zstd --threads 0`.

name: zsteg
description: Steganography detection tool for PNG and BMP file formats. It detects LSB steganography, ZLIB-compressed data, OpenStego, Camouflage, and LSB with the Eratosthenes set. More information: <https://github.com/zed-0xff/zsteg>.

name: zsync
description: Partial/differential file downloader. HTTPS is not supported - use HTTP URLs only. See also: `rsync`. More information: <https://manned.org/zsync>.

name: zypper
description: SUSE & openSUSE package management utility. For equivalent commands in other package managers, see <https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Pacman/Rosetta>. More information: <https://en.opensuse.org/SDB:Zypper_manual>.
